title: pumpkin soup
directions: Cut pumpkin into chunks and remove seeds and fiber.
Pare off any bumpy outer skin.
Cook in water until tender.
Drain; put through sieve.

title: apple and cranberry casserole
directions: Mix topping and spread on top of apples and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Set cranberries and sugar overnight.
Mix next 4 ingredients to the cranberries and add whipped cream as desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a
medium
saucepan,
melt margarine.
Add onion and saute. Add
mustard and Worcestershire.
Stir and add vinegar and brown sugar.
Add ketchup, water and Tabasco.
Simmer over low heat
for a few minutes.
Great for spareribs, chicken or pork.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Place cooked potatoes in baking dish.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix vanilla and water.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° until very hot (about 20 minutes).

title: cherry nut christmas cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt and add.
Roll into small balls.
Roll each ball in chopped nuts.
Push 1/2 candied cherry into center of each and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: sausage
directions: Mix together.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
Ready to eat or freeze.
Make patties or balls.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir dry ingredients with wire whip. Melt butter in 11 x 7 inch pan. Pour melted butter and milk into dry ingredients, stir until smooth. Pour back into baking pan. Sprinkle evenly with berries. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, butter, vanilla and egg in a bowl.
Stir in flour.
Mix well. Press dough evenly over bottom of 12-inch pizza pan.
Make a rim on edges (leave about 1/2-inch space to edge of pan or it will run over).
Bake crust 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Return to oven until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into slices.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 3-quart covered casserole and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not open until done.

title: good and easy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake 55 minutes in tube pan in a 300° oven.

title: rattlesnake chili(serves 6)
directions: Heat oil and saute onion, green peppers and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Add beef and rattlesnake.
Brown and cook until done, about 15 minutes.
Stir in spices, beans, tomatoes and paste.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Add water and return to a boil.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May be baked in muffin pans, but for a lesser time.)
Keeps well in freezer.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cheese, onion sauce and milk; drain shrimp.
Prepare catsup and horseradish together.
Add horseradish gradually to desired taste.
Position cheese on plate.
Top with shrimp.
Add sauce over all.
Serve with crackers.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and egg.
Then add raisins and liquid.
Sift in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Grease a cookie sheet and spread mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: aunt vera's zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cauliflower and cream cheese sauce
directions: Clean and cut up into bite-size pieces the cauliflower. Microwave.
In skillet, melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir in 3 heaping tablespoonfuls flour.
Add liquified cream cheese (adding milk with mixture).
Add garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Keep adding milk to gravy consistency.
Cook until thick.
Pour over cooked cauliflower.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl; add Jell-O pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 of the cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
May be made ahead or used immediately.

title: vanilla homemade ice cream
directions: You will also need an ice cream freezer.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Add enough milk to form the consistency of a cake mix.
Heat to a low boil, stirring constantly.
Serve on hot, buttered canned biscuits.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Put
sugar,
milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Bring to rolling
boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Set aside and blend in oats, peanut
butter and vanilla.
Drop onto wax paper.
Makes about 40 large cookies.

title: meat loaf (microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup.
Spoon into microwaveable dish.
Cook on High in microwave for 6 to 10 minute, depending on amount of hamburger.
Turn dish every 2 minutes. Drizzle catsup over top of loaf.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: fig preserves(century-old recipe)
directions: Make a syrup of cold water and sugar, using a little brown sugar, if desired, and bring syrup to a boil.
Sprinkle soda over figs.
Add boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse figs well.
Peel, if desired.
Add to syrup and boil for one hour.
Remove fruit, pack in hot containers, fill with boiling syrup and process immediately for 5 minutes in boiling water and for 10 minutes in the oven at 250°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry together meat, onion, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper; drain grease.
Grate cheese.
Brown flour in oil and add 1/2 teaspoon of cumin and oregano.
Add to meat mixture.
Fry tortillas; dip in Las Palmas sauce.
Fill with meat filling; add 1 olive and some cheese.
Roll up and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour Las Palmas over top.
Add any leftover olives and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: condensed milk
directions: Let stand in the refrigerator 2 hours or long. (Also to make powdered sugar, put granulated sugar in a blender and blend until fine.)

title: joyce's onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Save 3 tablespoons of crackers for topping.
Place rest in bottom of a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Remove onions from pan with slotted spoon.
Place a layer over cracker crumbs; add a layer of soup.
Alternate onions and soup in layers until full.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over onions and soup.
Top with cheese and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey, then add enough powdered milk until it makes a good workable mix.
Have kids help.
Play, then eat to clean up!

title: vanilla graham cracker surprise
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed on package (set aside).
Mix whipped cream (set aside).

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13- inch pan as directed.
Mix Jell-O in 2 separate cups with 1 cup boiling water each.
With a fork, poke holes in cake.
With a tablespoon, spoon Jell-O liquid in alternately diagonal bands 3 inches wide, across entire cake.
When completely cool, frost with frosting or Cool Whip and top with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: no-cook candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Put on board and knead until perfectly smooth and satiny.
Tint with food coloring if desired.
Shape and use as desired in making any of the following candies.
Store fondant airtight if not being used at once.
Will keep several days at room temperature.
Yield: About 1 1/3 pounds.

title: fat man's misery
directions: Mix crumb mixture and butter together.
Put 2/3 of this in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk with mixer.
Add ice cream, whip for 1 minute or a little longer.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Spoon Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle remainder of crumb mixture on top.
Crush candy bars and put on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat all
cheeses in bowl until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans
and beat.
Form into balls and roll in chopped pecans.
Will
form
average size balls.
Can be frozen.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar.
Bring to a slow boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and stir well.
Seal in jars or freeze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice.
Add strawberries and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cookie type pie crust and freeze.
Remove 10 minutes before serving.

title: italian delight
directions: Drain cooked spaghetti in cold water. Brown onion and green pepper in oil in large frying pan.
Add meat in small chunks. Brown well.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Place in baking pan and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: salad delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with hot water.
Add marshmallows (cut in half).
Crumble cream cheese and add to mixture.
Add pineapple. Fold in whipped cream and pecans.
Pour into square pan.
When set, cut into squares.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the spinach, strawberries and onions together well.

title: sausage and squash casserole
directions: Cook sausage and garlic together and drain.
Cook squash until done, then drain.
Stir in squash and all other ingredients except eggs.
Fold in the eggs.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good with regular summer squash or zucchini squash.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut candy
directions: Place chips and peanut butter in an 8-cup glass microwave bowl.
Microwave on Medium-high for 5 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Add crumbs and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Drop into paper cups and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion,
bell pepper and celery in stick of butter in skillet.
Add
broccoli,
cheese, soup and rice.
Heat well over medium
heat.
Pour
into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dream cycle cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Then add 1/2 box orange Jell-O and French vanilla pudding.
Bake at 350° until done in pan of choice.

title: grandma's icing
directions: Stir in milk and flour over double boiler.
Cook until thickens (resembles mashed potatoes).
Set aside and let cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream 1/4 cup butter and 3/4 cup sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add beaten egg and stir in mixture of 2 cups of flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread evenly into a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine remaining 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and cinnamon in a small mixing bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over blueberry layer.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.
Serve with milk.

title: avocado pie
directions: Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Put mixture in a baked pie shell (use either graham or regular shell).
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
(I use sewing thread.)
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup of sour cream mixture for frosting. Spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: mama naff's mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix and let set until firm.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until slightly brown at 375°.
Reduce heat to 325°; bake until firm.

title: green dragon dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado.
Mix with remaining ingredients and blend well.
Add onion, if desired.
Chill before serving.

title: pickled pigs' feet
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep, blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, cherries, almond extract and eggs.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, margarine and milk; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir until smooth.
Pour over hot cake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature. Mix all ingredients together; put into pie crusts and freeze. Keep any leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Heat oven to
Sift
dry ingredients into a bowl. Stir in milk and melted shortening.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle with
mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot water
over
entire batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to the top and chocolate sauce goes to bottom. Serve
warm with whipped cream.
Serves 9.	I make it without nuts if I don't have some.

title: heavenly strawberry
directions: Tear angel food cake apart.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together.
Then mix strawberries and glaze together.
Pour over cake.

title: german gulasch
directions: Cut the beef in cubes.
Cut the onions and bacon in cubes. Heat bacon until translucent, not brown.
Add the meat and brown in two to three portions.
Add the onions and cook until well blended and soft.
Add tomato paste, paprika, salt, pepper and cumin to the meat mixture.
Stir well.
Then add the liquid. Cover pot tightly and simmer on low heat for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: strada
directions: Cut crust from bread. Place 6 slices of bread in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan. Brown sausage. Sprinkle shredded cheese on bread, then sausage. Top with other 6 slices of bread. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.

title: banana cake
directions: Flour nuts and chips before putting in batter.
Mix all ingredients very well, especially bananas.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Grease only bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double recipe for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: squash rolls
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well. Add eggs and cracker crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Spoon out mixture. Roll lightly in cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat until firm.
Makes 10 rolls.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix the sour cream and mayonnaise (do not use salad dressing). Add other ingredients and mix well.
Best to make ahead and let set a while.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together salt, flour, baking soda and powder.
Combine bananas, sour cream and nuts.
Combine butter-sugar mixture with dry ingredients.
Add banana mixture. Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours (baking time may vary).

title: southern pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) one spoon at a time, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple; blend well.
Pour into greased large pan.
Place in cold oven; turn temperature to 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back.
Let stand a few minutes; run knife around edge.
Remove carefully to rack.
Combine 1/4 cup butter, 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar and 1 cup drained pineapple and pour over hot cake.

title: orange salad
directions: Boil pear juice and dissolve jello.
Add softened cheese and dissolve.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and chopped pears.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and arrange in a 4 x 8-inch casserole dish, top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese then bread crumbs and put butter on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: fig muffins
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, butter and sugar until fluffy;
add milk and figs; mix about 1 minute.
Mix Bisquick mix, cinnamon and cloves together; add to creamed mixture and beat 1 minute. Grease muffin
pan and bake at 350° until it is a light brown, and bounces back when touched.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bring to boil water and oleo.
Add oatmeal; cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Add eggs to oatmeal, then add to dry ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Blanche cabbage 2 minutes in salt water; drain.
Blend in 3 tablespoons butter, dill, salt and pepper; set aside.
Saute mushrooms, 3 tablespoons butter and onion.
Stir into cabbage; add the tomato sauce and sour cream.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: popcorn ole
directions: Sprinkle seasonings over corn.
Stir until mixed.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to box directions.
Make 2 layers.
When cool, cut layers in half with thread, making four layers.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Cook potatoes in water; peel and mash.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before done, put the topping on.
Bake for the rest of the 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cook 1 cup raisins and save the raisin water to use for the liquid in these cookies.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and bake in a quick oven.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 cup cold water and add vanilla ice cream.
Pour over cake and let stand 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Meanwhile, mix jello with 1 cup hot water and add to thawed strawberries (let thicken a little bit).
Pour over cake mixture and let stand overnight.
Cut in squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix together and boil 10 minutes.
Put in pint or 1/2 pint jars.
If mixture is hot, jars will seal.
If you get a lot of juice, strain and put in separate jar.
Makes good Bloody Mary mix.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: basic two egg yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease and flour pans (2 to 4). Sift into large bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening. Pour in 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Beat low to moisten flour mixture, then beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl as necessary. Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk. Beat 1 1/2 minutes on medium speed. Divide batter evenly into pans. Bake until done (2 layers, bake 25 to 30 minutes; shorten time if thinner layers are used). Cool a little before removing from pans. Cool completely before icing.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, and pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or til done.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together except half of the cheese.
Place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered 40 - 60 minutes at 350.

title: curried honey chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook to thicken. Pour ingredients over skinless chicken thighs and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto tins and bake slowly at 250°.
These cookies stay moist and fruity for a long time and are loved by children.

title: mexican fiesta casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Stir in garlic, chili, cumin, salt, sugar, oregano, tomato sauce and water.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Simmer 15 minutes. Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, onion, black olives, avocado, sour cream, hot sauce, shredded cheese and Doritos.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put sliced strawberries in pie shell. Boil sugar, flour and water until thick. Add jello. Remove from heat and cool. Pour over strawberries in pie shell. Chill in refrigerator until set. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: turkey (chicken) loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and flavorings. Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Divide in two.
Chill. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or just until edges start to brown.
Brush with egg white and water mixture and sprinkle with sugar before baking or cool and ice.

title: christmas relish
directions: In food processor, chop vegetables.
Allow to stand 2 1/2 hours after salting.
Drain excess juice (save for soup stock). Boil together 4 cups sugar, 3 cups vinegar and 1 ounce mustard seed.
Pour hot liquid over tomato mix.
Let stand 2 hours.
Pack into jars.
Boil filed jars upside-down until sealed, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Good with meats or vegetables.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in a 2 1/2 greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly brown.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: In salad bowl, blend vinegar, soy, sugar and ginger.
Stir in oil and onion.
Add green peppers and sesame seed and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kona banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mary's favorite icing
directions: Combine milk and flour in a saucepan.
Cook until thick. Cover and refrigerate.
Beat butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Beat for 10 minutes. Frost cooled cake chocolate cake or any kind.

title: mom's favorite punch with or without alcohol
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Just before using, slowly pour in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.
May garnish with frosted Tokay grapes.
You may add champagne instead of water for added "punch."
(Serves 10.)

title: pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with nuts. Slice bread in 12 pieces and arrange in pan.
Combine dry vanilla pudding, butter, brown sugar, milk and cinnamon in saucepan. Place on medium heat and bring to a boil.
Pour liquid over bread and let rise for 2 hours or until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 12 large rolls.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Soften the yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over oats in a large bowl and let stand until lukewarm.
Add oil, yeast, salt, sugar and nuts and mix well.
Add the flour and mix thoroughly.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead well and place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes or until done.
May grease top with oleo or oil.

title: caramel pie
directions: Remove labels from cans.
Cook cans in boiling water for 2 hours.
Cover cans when opening them so the liquid does not burn you.
Pour condensed milk in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: corn bread-coated fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Turn under any thin edges of fish.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish (use an 8 x 8 x 8-inch baking dish for low wattage ovens) arrange thicker portions of fish fillets toward outer edges of the dish.
Brush fish with buttermilk or yogurt.
In a small mixing bowl cook margarine on 100% power (High) about 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in stuffing mix, salt and red pepper.
Spoon stuffing mixture over fish fillets.
Cook fish, uncovered, on High for 4 to 7 minutes (7 to 9 minutes for low-wattage ovens) or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Give the dish a half-turn after 3 minutes.
Serves 4; 4 g fat; 50 mg cholesterol.
A good quick microwave dish.

title: crusty dill spears
directions: Heat 1 inch oil in heavy skillet to 400°.
In bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and garlic powder; stir in milk, pickle juice and egg.
Dip pickles in batter to coat.
Fry in small batches, 2 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Makes 16 spears.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix; shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: summer cooler
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with sugar and 1/2 gallon of water. Add pineapple juice and place in freezer until slushy. Stir occasionally so it will not freeze solid. Before serving, fill gallon pitcher with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir well, then add milk and margarine.
Cook until it clings to sides of saucepan.
Remove from heat, then add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix until peanut butter melts.
Place newspaper covered with waxed paper onto countertop.
Dip by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Makes 12 cookies, then go over the 12 cookies until you have used all the mixture. Let cool and place cookies onto platter.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have cream cheese, butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese well.
Add eggs 2 at a time.
Beat well after each time.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time; beat well.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Frost with Cool Whip and additional nuts, if desired.

title: crab-chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix cheese, chestnuts, crabmeat and green onion together.
Add garlic and curry powder.
Fold in enough mayo to moisten mixture. Split each biscuit into thirds and place on cookie sheet.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoonful of crab mixture on each biscuit.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate together the cabbage, carrots and onion.
Mix in raisins, sugar, lemon juice, dressing and salt and pepper.
Mix together.

title: ham barbecue
directions: In oleo, saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add catsup, water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until thick.
Add ham.
Makes 5 sandwiches. Can be doubled.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crust and strawberries and boil until thick, stirring as it cooks.
Let cool.
Bake pie crust. Cool.
Spread bottom with part of pie filling.
Put in strawberries.
Pour remainder of filling over berries. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer for 5 minutes.
Knead together dinner roll dough.
Press dough onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, forming shell in pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake shell at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cover with meat mixture; top with processed cheese cubes.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Remove from oven and top with lettuce, tomato and olives.
Serve with sour cream, if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian beef in crockpot
directions: Cook in crockpot. Place all ingredients together in crockpot.. Cook on high heat for 8 hours.

title: oven chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients together except noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Sprinkle noodles on top.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal crisp(quick and easy)
directions: Spread apples in greased 9-inch dish.
Mix oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over apples. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes.
Serves 4-6.

title: mexican garden chowder
directions: Combine salsa, beans, water and corn in 3-quart saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium low and gradually stir in half & half.
Add cheese and potato flakes.
Stir occasionally. Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes or until chowder thickens slightly. Garnish each serving with a sprig of fresh cilantro and serve with corn chips.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Makes
close to 20 dozen cookies and are very good. Bake at 350 for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the ultimate casserole
directions: Cook pasta in 2-quart or larger pan.
As it cooks, add meat or fish and mixed vegetables.
(Best if in the last 5 minutes.) Drain and put mixture back in pan.
Add soup, cheese (if used) and milk.
Mix well.

title: crock-pot cranberry pork roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
(Boneless or pork loin roast may be used.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased 3-quart casserole at 400° for 1 hour.
This will be thin.
Thickens in baking.
Stir once while baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and fruit cocktail; place in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows, 2 packages pudding mix (just powder, not made as directed).
Drain 1/2 can pineapple.
Proceed to put juice from 1/2 the can into the mixture with the pineapple. Mix well with large spoon.
Return to refrigerator for 20 minutes to set.
Serve and enjoy!

title: emily carter jone's butter cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Take wax paper and make 3 long rolls.
Chill and then cut into slices.
Place cookie dough on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
These are very good.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, garlic salt and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 10 to 12.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Put cut up chicken in pan and coat with butter. Cover with 6 slices of cheese.
Mix can of soup with milk and pour mixture over chicken.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening; beat until smooth.
Cool. Sift flour and salt in.
Mold into a soft dough.

title: garlic gouda cheese spread
directions: Mince garlic in processor.
Add wine.
Soak a couple of minutes.
Add cheese and process until smooth.
While processing, season with chili powder, paprika and parsley.
Serve on crackers. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together sugar, salad oil, nuts and pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with other mixture.
Bake in a large oblong pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat canapes
directions: In
small
bowl
mix first 5 ingredients.
Toast bread; trim off crusts and cut into squares.
Arrange on cookie sheet and top with about 1 teaspoon crab mixture.
Spread evenly and sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 5 or 6 inches from heat for 2 or 3 minutes, until bubbly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add oil, then the vanilla, carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: Finish filling freezer with milk.
Freezer uses ice cubes and 1 cup table salt.

title: ham and noodles
directions: In skillet over medium heat, saute onion in oleo until tender. Add ham; cook and stir until heated through.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for 1 minute.
Turn heat on low, gradually stir in sour cream.
Add the mushrooms; cook and stir until thickened for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles and garnish with parsley.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put ground beef in bottom of 9 x 13 inch dish. Spread soup over meat. Cover soup with grated cheese. Top with tater tots. bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except gravy.
Shape into 6 oblong patties.
In skillet, brown patties in shortening.
Pour off fat. Add gravy.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk and eggs.
Add milk and egg mixture gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in apple strips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot fat for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Will also need heavy-duty Reynolds aluminum foil wrap.

title: marinated corn-bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over veggies.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.

title: ham 'n' cheese rolls
directions: Cream together butter, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Spread on cut open rolls. Top with ham and grated cheese. Place tops back on rolls. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. If frozen, 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, slice
and core apples. Cut into 8 slices.
Tear biscuits into 3 layers each and wrap around apples.
Place in pan. Mix water, sugar and butter. Bring to a boil.
Pour over apples and sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fire house potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes. Cut in half lengthways. Sprinkle cookie sheet with season salt, covering the bottom. Lay potatoes face down on cookie sheet. Put a pat of butter or margarine on each potato. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender. Good hot or cold.

title: coconut pie
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs; blend in milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, vanilla and coconut.
Add to 2 slightly greased pie pans and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. clary's pecan balls
directions: Mix everything in bowl, except confectioners sugar.
Mix with hands.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven at 375°.
Roll balls about 1 inch and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set (but not brown).
Let cool 1 minute and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 20 balls.

title: easy roast dinner
directions: Cover 1/2 to 3/4 of roast with soup.
Crumble onion rings over roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Add fresh onion if desired.
After 3 hours, add potatoes and carrots.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine top 3 ingredients and 2 packages chipped beef.
Shape into ball.
Cover outside of ball with remaining package of chipped beef.

title: passover matzo farfel kugel
directions: Cover farfel with hot water, then drain.
Add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, eggs, crumbs, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, salt and oregano.
Shape into loaf and place half in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put Mozzarella over top and spread rest on top. Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon sauce over the loaf and more Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven until melted.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and cream with Crisco.
Add sugar, 4 eggs and salt; beat until fluffy.
Add flour and almond extract.
Sprinkle with sugar and slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on ungreased jelly roll pan 10 x 15-inch; make sure to press all perforations closed and slightly up the sides of pan so it won't shrink; prick with fork.
Bake at 375° until golden.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch party mix together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle all other ingredients evenly on top of cheese.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cube bread and saute slowly in the butter.
Add pineapple, flour, sugar and the eggs.
Stir into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon-pineapple cake
directions: Bake according to cake box directions.
Let cool 5 minutes. Poke holes all over top of cake and pour can of crushed pineapple (juice and all) over cake.
Let cool completely.

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and cinnamon and chill until thickened.
Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Spoon into 6-cup mold or bowl.
Chill until firm, about four hours.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Serve with bread cubes or crackers.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; spoon into greased cupcake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a skillet, cook green pepper, onion, garlic, basil and rosemary in hot oil until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice, chopped tomato, salt, pepper and 2 cups water.
Cook covered over low heat for about 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Makes 6 servings.
For family gatherings or reunions, double all ingredients.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and peppers until soft.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth and seasonings.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Put soup into bowls.
Add crumbled chips and grated cheese.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple; dissolve lime jello in boiling water; cool. Add pineapple and cream cheese.
Lastly, add whipped cream.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can be made overnight.

title: chocolate-cherry cake
directions: Mix in eggs; then fold in pie filling.
Bake as directed on box.

title: goetta
directions: Buy a bag of pinhead oatmeal.
Follow the directions on the bag with these exceptions:

title: miracle frosting
directions: Boil milk and flour until thick.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients.
Beat 10 minutes.
Spread on cake.
(Food coloring may be added.)

title: ham and swiss stromboli
directions: Unroll dough on a greased baking sheet.
Place ham over dough to within 1/2-inch of edges; sprinkle evenly with onion tops, bacon and cheese.
Roll up jellyroll style, starting with a long side.
Pinch seams to seal and tuck ends under.
Place, seam side down, on baking sheet.

title: quick fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl. Microwave 3-5 min., Stirring twice.
Pour into waxed lined pan. Put in refrigerator until hard. Remove, Cut.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Heat to a boil.
Add boiling liquid to gelatin and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Cool.
Stir occasionally.
Whip cream. Put cream, carrot and pineapple into cooled gelatin.
Pour into molds.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt and shortening.
Dissolve in boiling water.
When shortening is liquid, add 2 eggs.
Beat with whisk. Add yeast and water.
Mix well.
Add flour, mixing well.
Put in a large bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours. Take out on floured surface.
Knead lightly.
Roll out into large circle.
Cut into pie shape and roll up large side to point for crescent rolls or place small balls (three) into muffin pan; butter with brush.
Allow to rise until double in bulk, about 1 to 2 hours in draft-free area.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured pan.
Bake one hour or until done.

title: cold spiced fruit
directions: Cut orange slices in half, cover with water and simmer until rind is tender.
Drain well and set aside.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put in blender the hot peppers, bell peppers and onions. Blend until peppers and onions are finely chopped.
Combine vinegar, sugar, onions and peppers.
Bring to a boil, pour into jars and seal.

title: amish dressing
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together the bread, potatoes, carrots, celery and parsley.
Stir in well beaten eggs.
Add liquid, which may be chicken broth or milk.
Add chicken; toss lightly.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown.

title: fish stew
directions: Saute garlic, onion and green pepper in olive oil until onion is limp. Add tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add cubed fish and shrimp. Coul also add 1/4 cup chopped parsley and 1 dozen butter clams in the shell.
Bring back to a boil, cover and simmer for 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Steam or bake fresh pumpkin and put it through a sieve. Canned pumpkin is ready to use.
Add remaining ingredients in the order given.
Pour into a crust-lined pan and bake.
Use a high temperature at first (450°) to cook the bottom and sides of crust. Reduce the temperature and continue cooking at 325°
until a silver knife inserted in the center will come out clean.
Do not let the pie boil as that will make it watery.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Blend soup with 1/2 cup water.
Measure 1/4 cup soup mixture (save the rest).
Mix with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and onion.
Shape into balls (1-inch).
Brown in 1 teaspoon of oil. Drain off fat.
Add remaining soup mixture and cook over medium to low heat.
Stir now and then.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: hamburger wellington
directions: Mix ingredients together, mold into 10 x 12-inch rectangle on foil.
Arrange ham and cheese on meat rectangle, then roll it like jelly roll and seal edges together. Cover with rolls and brush with egg and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix cake as directed on box. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake batter over pecans and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Mix will be thick.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over cake batter (do not spread).
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.
Serve from pan.
Do not try to turn out on plate (will not stick together).

title: chicken salad deluxe
directions: Mix mayonnaise and soy sauce; pour over other ingredients that have been well mixed.
Serve on lettuce leaf cups or pineapple halves for a special ladies luncheon.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Sear roast quickly in butter.
Simmer with cloves, bouquet garni, garlic and parsley.
Cook roast slowly in wine and stock for 4 to 5 hours.
Saute mushrooms separately.
Saute onions in additional butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Slice roast; garnish with mushrooms and onions.
Strain sauce and serve with roast.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter, stirring constantly after mixture boils.
Boil 5 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and kisses.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: coconut dream dessert
directions: Crush crackers fine. Add melted margarine. Save 1/2 of mixture for topping.
Pour half of the crumb mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix milk with instant pudding. Add softened ice cream to pudding. Whip the Dream Whip as directed on package. Spread on top of pudding. Add rest of crumb mixture on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vince's favorite pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl mix cream cheese, milk and sugar with a wire whisk or mixer until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup cold milk in bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk or mixer for 1 minute until thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until smooth. Spread over cream cheese and whipped topping layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: oven french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan in hot oven (425°).
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix eggs and orange juice; dip bread slices in mixture until bread is well soaked but doesn't fall apart.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until set.
Invert onto serving plates; serve with maple syrup.

title: dirt pie
directions: You will also need a plastic flower and a new, clean flowerpot.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough on pizza pan for crust.
Whip together and spread on crust the cream cheese, sour cream and xxxx sugar. Arrange strawberries, cut in half, on top of cream mixture.
Top with Glaze.
Add whipped cream.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for one hour.
Add kidney beans and heat thoroughly. Serve.

title: chicken bono "d"
directions: Brush chicken breasts lightly with vegetable oil.
Dip in Italian bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Put thin slices of onion rings on top.
Also pieces of green pepper, strips or chunks. Cover with 1/2 to 3/4 cup canned tomatoes, not much juice.
Bake at 300° to 350° for about 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice or buttered noodles.

title: beth's lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook celery, onion, and garlic in drippings until tender.
Add ground beef and cook over medium heat until red color disappears and meat is crumbly, not hard.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste to meat.
Season with salt, sugar, cayenne pepper and oregano.
Place bay leaf on top of mixture. Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Don't stir.
Remove bay leaf. Meanwhile, cook noodles as directed on box.
Arrange 1/2 noodles in bottom of 12x8x2 inch baking dish (3 quart).
Spoon in half of meat, then half of cottage cheese, then half of mozzarella. Repeat layers;
noodles, meat, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and reserve 1 cup broth.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Combine chili powder, garlic salt, soups, broth and Rotel tomatoes.
Place 1/2 chicken in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with 1/2 soup mixture, cover with Fritos, onion and green pepper. Add grated cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zesty macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add tomatoes. Enjoy.

title: butterscotch heaven
directions: Note:
You can use chocolate pudding for butterscotch.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: meringue for banana pudding or pies
directions: Beat egg whites until firm with cream of tartar.
Add sugar. Top banana pudding.
Bake until brown.

title: strawberry-chocolate meringues(low calorie, low cholesterol, low-fat and low sodium)
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line cookie sheet with cooking parchment paper or aluminum foil.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in medium bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Fold in chocolate.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and spices in water for 10 minutes or until rhubarb is mushy.
Strain in sieve.
Add sugar while mixture is hot, stirring until thoroughly dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: penoche frosting
directions: In a medium size cooking pan, add all ingredients at one time. Stir over low heat and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Time 1 minutes after start of boiling.
Remove from heat and beat until it reaches a good spreading consistency.
Add a little vanilla.
Very good for your favorite chocolate cake.
Covers a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Place sugar and chocolate in food processor and process until finely chopped.
Add margarine.
Process until blended.
Add boiling water and process until blended, scraping to be sure all is well mixed.
Pour into 4 cup microwavable measuring cup and cook on High until it bubbles, indicating it is boiling, at least twice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Dissolve pudding mix with crushed pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip and other ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: clo's chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix all well and cook in double boiler or over very low heat until it thickens.
Pour into large 10-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and bake in hot oven (about 400°) until slightly brown, about 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine cooked macaroni with all other ingredients and mix well. Top with a little extra shredded cheese and cook on low in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: coconut sponge cake
directions: Beat until creamy first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, salt and baking powder to creamed mixture.
Heat milk and butter until milk is hot.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° until
cake is done (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: 1949 steak, country style(american)
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and dredge with the seasoned flour.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large frying pan and add the onions and mushrooms.
Cook until the onions are tender and the mushrooms are just slightly browned.
Remove the onions and mushrooms from the pan and set aside.
Add the remaining 1/4 cup butter and when melted, add the steak and brown on both sides. Stir in the rest of the ingredients, along with the mushroom mixture.
Cover and cook until meat is tender enough to cut with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Add the onion soup mix, then the soup and water, mixed.
Add chicken, putting chicken pieces (salted) on top.
Cook, covered, in oven for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover last 30 minutes to brown.
Cook at 350° in 2 1/2 to 3-quart bowl or pan.

title: overnite cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients, then add nuts and flour. Mix all together.
Roll out in 4 or more balls or rolls. Refrigerate overnight, then slice and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: microwave chinese clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch
morsels
in 2 quart casserole.
Heat on Full power (700°)
to
3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir together until
smooth.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by
teaspoons
onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: prices barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Blend well.
Use on meat, chicken or sausage.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil 20 minutes and add 1 tablespoon celery salt.
This keeps a long time unrefrigerated.

title: easy cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add cheese.
Cut in shortening and add milk to make soft dough.
Place on a floured board.
Knead lightly for a few seconds, using as little flour as possible. Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes. Makes 14 biscuits.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Bring concentrate to boil.
Combine margarine, cornstarch, spices, and enough concentrate to make smooth.
Stir this into boiling concentrate and cook until clear and thickened.
Pour over apples and stir until coated.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes and then reduce heat to 375° and bake another 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle in the warm water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until all the flour is moistened and dough almost cleans side of bowl.
Gather dough into a ball; divide into 12 equal balls.
Shape into balls; cover and let rest 20 minutes.
Roll each ball on floured surface into 6-inch circle.
Heat ungreased 8-inch skillet or griddle over medium-high heat until hot.
Cook tortillas until dry around the edges and blisters appear on surface, about 2 minutes on each side.
Stack tortillas, placing waxed paper between each.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Yields 12 tortillas.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put the rest of the can of onions on top.
Put back in oven and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: brownies
directions: Sift baking powder, flour and salt; beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually; mix in Wesson oil, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour, etc. all at once.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn batter into a 7 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: circle bear confetti freeze
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread whipped topping over crust; freeze until firm. Spread ice cream over frozen whipped topping; freeze until firm. Spread chilled chocolate topping over ice cream.
Freeze. Sprinkle with mints just before serving.
Garnish with animal crackers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; boil until tender.
Drain.
Combine milk, salt, cornstarch and margarine.
Bring to a boil and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour over cooked potatoes and bake at 350° until it starts to brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar, beating 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: a mix to put over cream cheese
directions: Mix together and store in jars.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.
When serving, spoon over cream cheese.

title: baked halibut with sour cream dill sauce(from 1975 edition)
directions: Place halibut steaks in shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with marjoram.
Add wine or chicken broth.
Drizzle steaks with melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic. Place a lemon slice over each steak.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Serve steaks hot or cold with Sour Cream Dill Sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauteed apples with pecan slices
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and cinnamon in a large skillet; cook over medium-high heat until butter melts.
Add apple slices, turning to coat.
Saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Transfer apples to a serving plate.
Add cream and rum seasoning to skillet, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture is thickened and reduced to about 2/3 cup.
Stir in dates and reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Arrange apple slices around 4 bowls.
Put ice cream in the middle and spoon sauce over apple slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apple slices in a shallow baking dish.
Cream the butter; blend in sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in cereal. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serve warm. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper; add water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add soup, cheese and corn; stir until cheese is melted.
Do not boil. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mr. jennings' refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, green pepper, onions and salt in ice water, making sure the water covers the vegetables.
Let them stand one hour in water, then drain.

title: scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients and blend in margarine.
Add eggs and milk.
Form into soft ball.
Press lightly to 3/4-inch on floured cloth.
Cut with large round cutter.
Mix remaining egg yolk and 1 tablespoon sugar and brush tops.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with onion and celery until done. Cut into bite size chunks. In a double boiler over low heat, stir together mayonnaise, chicken broth and cheese. Stir constantly until cheese is melted. In a casserole, layer chicken, peas and pearl onions then sauce. Repeat until all are used. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: tuna-corn bread casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted, boiling water until barely tender. Drain.
Add onion, tuna, salt, pepper, soup and milk.
Heat to boiling.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in buttered casserole.
Makes 4 average servings.

title: ham and potato salad
directions: Cook and then cube potatoes.
Cook and then chop green beans. Combine potatoes, beans, ham and onions.
Mix vinegar, mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables and toss lightly.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over carrots and toss to coat.

title: bean bake(calico)
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in slow cooker or bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover for juicier beans.

title: honey cake
directions: Mix sugar, honey, vanilla, Crisco oil and chopped nuts with a spoon.
Mix together sifted flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; add to honey mixture.
Beat eggs; add pumpkin gradually and alternately. Grease and flour large, flat pan and bake 18 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Chop vegetables up.
Mix all together, then add dressing and bacon bits.
Best if made the night before.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together. Set overnight.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a large bowl. Boil oleo, crisco, coco, and water. Pour over sugar and flour. Add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon, soda, and vanilla. Mix with a spoon. Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes. Do not grease the pan. Ice with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nutmeats.
Press mixture into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked fish steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove skin from fish, cut meat from bones.
Cut 4 (10 x 12-inch) pieces of heavy-duty foil, use oil to grease center of each piece of foil.
Place a steak on each piece of foil.
Top each steak with slices of onion, potato and carrot. Salt and pepper.
Using drugstore wrap, fold each piece separately. Put on cookie sheet and bake until fish flakes and is tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Heat topping over medium heat until it boils, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie crust.
Arrange pecans on top and chill.
Cook milk and pie mix over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool (not cook, cool); stir twice.
Pour over nuts in crust.
Cover surface with plastic wrap.
Chill 3 hours. Remove wrap and put Cool Whip around top.
Drizzle with additional caramel topping and pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and cook squash until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and mix until butter melts.
Add sour cream and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add seasoning packets from stuffing mix; mix well.
Add stuffing mix.
Blend in cheeses.
Use large roasting pan or lasagna pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: date balls
directions: Boil until thick, first four ingredients; cook long enough so you won't crack the sugar when you eat them.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: lime ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemony.
Add sugar gradually; definitely do this slowly.
Add cream and half or less of the milk. Pour into homemade ice cream freezer can and add milk until recipe fills the can to the fill line.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl and mix until evenly distributed throughout the cream cheese.
Form into a ball or log. Roll in the remaining chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans 8 hours or overnight.
Cook beans until tender in a large pot of water.
Saute in olive oil, chopped celery, garlic and onion.
Add to cooked beans.
Add tomato sauce or juice. Serve with cornbread.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add vanilla and orange flavorings. Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Spoon into greased loaf pan and bake at 300° about 1 hour. Yield: 1 loaf cake.

title: light freezer rolls
directions: Scald the milk.
Cool (lukewarm) and add the yeast; set aside. Beat in a bowl the eggs, sugar, shortening and salt. Add cooled milk mixture to bowl mixture.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour (not all at once).
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour by hand.
Knead on floured surface.
Place in a large bowl and cover with clean cloth.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and divide in 6 parts.
Roll out into 9-inch circles.
Brush with margarine and cut into pie wedges (6 to 8 per circle). Start at wide end and roll wedge to point.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, store in freezer bags. Can be kept in freezer for about 1 month.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen rolls.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls into bottom of a 13 x 9 pan.
Add any of the above in any amount.
Drain the sausage before adding. Pour the dozen eggs on just before baking.

title: raw radish dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend together cream cheese, lemon juice, dill weed, salt and garlic.
Add radishes and stir until blended. Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with radish rose and parsley if desired.
Serve with corn chips, other sturdy chips or crackers.

title: bean relish
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a big bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and let stand overnight.
Stir before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Tasty.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on top.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Cook rhubarb and orange peel in a minimal amount of water for about 10 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Mix until smooth. While stirring, slowly add to rhubarb mixture and cook until slightly thickened.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix package of red jello.
Chill until partially set. Meanwhile, grind the cranberries in food processor and mix with 2 cups of sugar; let stand.
It will be juicy.
Mix in pecans, marshmallows and grapes.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into the jello.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Chill until set.

title: caramel-apple sundae cheesecake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg. Add flour; mix well.
Spread dough onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate several hours.
Serves approximately 15 people.
Very good frozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat until smooth.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. Stir the flour mix into batter.
Peel, core and thickly slice apples.
Stir apples, walnuts and raisins into batter.
Turn into buttered, floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into the cake comes out clean.
Allow cake to cool briefly in pan (10 minutes) as this will make the outside crunchy. Turn cake onto rack and allow to cool completely.

title: banana apple cake
directions: Spray glass pan with Pam.
Mix oil, sugar and egg white.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pot, brown beef with onions and drain off excess grease. Add the tomato juice, corn, beans, tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Stir together well and heat throughout, but do not boil! Serve with tortilla chips, shredded Cheddar cheese and sour cream on top.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add all the other ingredients, except cheese.
Heat until warm through, then turn down low and add cheese to the top.
Put a lid on skillet until cheese is melted.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Mix 2 minutes. Grease and flour only bottom of pans.
Use 2 large bread pans or 5 small ones.
Small foil pans make 5 loaves.
Line bottom with parchment paper.
Saves time.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta chicken kiev(microwave)
directions: Power level: High (10).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Drop cabbage in boiling water.
Cook until most tender; drain. Mix soup, mayonnaise, margarine and cheese.
Mix well while heating.
Put half of cabbage in buttered casserole dish.
Add half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers of cabbage and soup.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the peaches and save juice.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sift together the sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour milk and vanilla over dry ingredients and mix.
Put batter in pan over butter.
Place peaches in batter.
Pour juice over all.
Sprinkle the cinnamon-sugar mixture over peaches.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add Miracle Whip.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with frozen hash browns.
Mix first 5 ingredients above and pour on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box (for 2 layers).
Split cake in halves when cooled.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut (reserve small amount of plain coconut to put on finished cake). Chill mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for frosting.
Spread rest between layers and on top of cake.	Combine sour cream mixture (1 cup) with Cool Whip and blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides. Sprinkle rest of coconut on cake.
Store in airtight container for 3 days in refrigerator before slicing.
Enjoy!

title: creamy chocolate icing
directions: In mixing bowl beat at medium speed until all ingredients are well blended.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions in broth from chicken.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together the first 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth. Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls or use a cookie press, if preferred.
If shaping into balls, use floured fork to flatten cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12
minutes or until edges are lightly brown.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: yummy sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir in flour, salt and soda last. These are too rich to roll out.
Drop by teaspoonful and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: mushroom cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Make a soft dough of mix and water.
Beat well.
Press dough in bottom of pan.
If you flour your hands, it'll work easier.

title: sherry's dessert
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then put 1/2 of vanilla pudding/Cool Whip combination over graham cracker layer.
Next, put another layer of graham crackers.
Next, the last half of vanilla pudding and Cool Whip mix.
Top off with a layer of graham crackers , covered over with 1 can of cherry pie filling (large size).

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (maybe longer, depending on your oven).
I usually make a double batch.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix in large bowl in the order given. Drop by large tablespoons.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Put peaches, 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla in a 9 x 12-inch pan; heat in oven until sugar is dissolved.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in a medium bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir every 30 seconds until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly on crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Pour over bananas in crust.
Spread with topping.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar to crushed sticks.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; arrange chicken, skin side down, in greased, shallow baking pan.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Put ingredients in large bowl. Mix dough; leave covered in bowl in the refrigerator overnight. Roll out; cut out biscuits. Let rise 1 hour in greased pan after cutting out. Bake at 450°.

title: texas salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Add drained beans, grated cheese and crushed Fritos.
Cover with Catalina dressing.

title: chicken with apples and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Saute apples and onions until tender.
Spoon evenly into 6 cups baking dish.
Rub chicken with salt, pepper and a little garlic powder.
Arrange on top of apples, overlapping slightly.
Combine shredded cheese, Parmesan, crumbs and thyme. Sprinkle evenly over top.
Drizzle cider over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: better than kisses cake
directions: Toss the chocolate chips and pecans in a tablespoon of the cake mix.
Beat the remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes, then fold in the chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until a tester inserted into cake comes out clean.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add sherbet and dissolve (over hot water).
Add juice (from pineapple and oranges), orange sections and pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: caramelized carrots
directions: Peel and slice the carrots.
Put in pan. Cover with water and parboil.
Drain the water and make a well in the middle of carrots. Add oleo. Add 1/4 cup hot water. Add sugar.
Spoon sauce mixture over carrots. Simmer until carrots are done. Add water, if needed.
You may add cinnamon.
It's easy enough for a kid to do.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly cream together sugar and shortening.
Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well and add nuts and raisins if you want. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet to cool.
Frost with your favorite vanilla frosting if desired or the frosting of your choice.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pioneer drumsticks(method:  stick)
directions: Mix beef, seasonings, eggs and cornflakes together thoroughly. Divide into 16 portions.
Wrap a portion around a green stick (thumb size) that has been peeled about 3 inches on the end.
Make meat long and thin (not in a ball); be sure there are no air spaces.
(Watch out for big pieces of cornflakes.)
Cook slowly over coals, turning frequently so all sides are evenly cooked. Twist slightly to remove from stick and serve in a roll.

title: applesauce spiced cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar
and extracts.
Sift together flour and other dry
ingredients.
Add
alternately with applesauce. Spoon batter into a 9
x
2-inch
baking pan (greased). Bake at 350° for about
35	minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in 9-inch round glass baking dish.
Microwave on medium for about 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar. Arrange pineapple on top.
Place a cherry in center of each pineapple slice.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over pineapple.
Microwave on low for 7 minutes.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 1 minute.
Turn out onto platter. Serve warm or cool.

title: fat-free brownies
directions: Dissolve coffee in 1/2 tablespoon water.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites and pecans.
Then beat 2 egg whites and fold into mixture.
Add pecans last.
Line pan with aluminum foil; spray.
(Use small brownie pan.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and save bacon.
Cut corn off of cobb, then scrape cobb to remove milky substance.
Add corn to bacon dripping, add water and cook until it is the consistency of cream corn.
If it thickens too much, add a little water.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream together cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Add flour. Make into a roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator.
It will keep up to one month.
Slice into thin wafers and bake at 350° (do not brown).

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon and water to 240° with candy thermometer. When temperature is met, add vanilla and nutmeats.
Stir until nuts are well coated. Turn out on waxed paper and separate.
Cool.

title: pecan banana smoothie
directions: In blender, puree all ingredients and pour into chilled glass. Serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Cut wax paper or foil for the bottom of 11 x 16-inch pan.
Spray with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on smooth muslin tea towel with powdered sugar sprinkled on it.
While still hot, roll up and let cool. When cool, unroll and remove towel; fill with filling.

title: mediterranean bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat together sugar and soft butter then add salt, eggs and yeast.
Beat in 2 cups flour.
Once mixed add 2 cups more flour and mix with spoon or hands.
Knead on floured board and put in greased bowl.
Let rise to double (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).	Note:

Dough will be sticky before kneading. Drain well and pat dry 1 cup each small ripe olives and green stuffed olives then slice.	Roll dough into a 14 x 16-inch rectangle.	Scatter olives evenly over dough and press in.	Roll tightly lengthwise and seal seams and ends well.
Note:
Not easy but water works fairly well to help seal seams.
Put on greased sheet and let rise again.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with whatever type of seeds you want.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese and caviar dip
directions: Add milk to the softened cream cheese and beat together until fluffy.
Beat in the chives and parsley.
Gently stir in half of the caviar into cheese mixture.
Place in a serving bowl and garnish with the remaining caviar.
For color, decorate outer edge of bowl with parsley sprigs.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of dip.
Serve with crisp, raw vegetables or thinly sliced toast points.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients; spread in casserole (8-inch square). Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with roll of Ritz crackers, crushed.
Spread on top of potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Can be prepared the night before.
Put topping on just before baking.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and 2 cups flour; mix well.
Use rest of flour (1 1/2 cups) to roll fruit and nuts in.
Add coconut.
Add all to batter and cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours or until tests done.

title: spicy crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in greased shallow baking dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat soups and add chicken.
Butter pan; layer chicken, then onion, then chips, then cheese.
Repeat layers and end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: lemon cheese ring
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Beat cheese and sugar with electric beater until blended.
Add milk, gradually and beat until blended.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool.
Beat into cheese mixture and add lemonade and beat until smooth.
Turn into 1 quart mold and chill until firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Triple this recipe for 3 chickens and use 2 onions.

title: cranberry sauce with cognac
directions: Cook together sugar and water until it boils.
Continue boiling 3 minutes, or until syrup thickens.
Toss in cloves, cinnamon, cranberries and orange rind and pulp.
Cook over low heat until cranberries start to pop.
Stir occasionally and remove from heat.
Remove cloves and cinnamon.
Add cognac; mix well and chill.

title: michael's favorite spinach cheese balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix in melted butter, crushed croutons, eggs, cheese and nutmeg.
Roll into 1 to 2-inch balls and place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper and freeze for at least 1 hour.
Bake frozen on lightly greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes, until firm, at 350°.
Watch carefully so bottoms don't brown to much.

title: sugar bows
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Sift together flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter and Crisco until particles are size of small peas.
Blend in 2 beaten eggs, sour cream, vanilla and the softened yeast.
Mix thoroughly. Cover; chill at least 2 hours.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine the ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Dot with butter; apply top crust.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: georgia pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
