Mix flour and nuts together, then add to first mixture.
Stir in pineapple. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Test with straw or wood pick.
Mix juice and powdered sugar; pour over hot cake.
Let cake cool completely in pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini about 1/4 inch thick and boil in water, then drain.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and saute carrots and onion until tender.
Fold in soup with sour cream and 1/2 the croutons. Gently fold drained zucchini and carrots and onions with soup mixture.
Place in a 7 x 11-inch greased pan; put remaining croutons on top.
Pour remaining melted butter over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except biscuit mix, with mixer until well blended.
Then, by hand, add Jiffy mix until smooth.
Then, with teaspoon, roll balls of cookies and put on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until browned.
Then cool.

title: cherry pineapple crunch cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in undrained pineapple; spread.
Pour in cherry pie filling; spread over pineapple.
Open cake mix and sprinkle over cherries and pineapple.
Cut stick of butter into small squares; place on top of cake mix.
Bake for given time and temperature on cake box.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes, mix flour salt, pepper, cheese in plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes in egg mixture.
Put oleo on cookie sheet and melt in oven.
Put potatoes in flour mixture and coat. Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.
Turn potatoes once.
When golden brown sprinkle with parsley if desired.

title: favorite potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes 1/2 hour.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Place 8 slices bread, edges together, in pan.
Combine first six ingredients.
Spread on slices.
Place second 8 slices of buttered bread on this.
Spread with mixture of soup and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with fresh fruit salad for bridge!
Serves 8.

title: irish brown soda bread(aran donn soide gaelach)
directions: Mix ingredients in mixing bowl. Stir in the buttermilk and beaten egg.
Knead sparingly on a floured surface. Shape into a cake and cut a deep cross in the surface.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven for 40 minutes. Alternatively, bake in a loaf tin. This recipe also applies to a white loaf made without meal or bran.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling	water; add sugar. Chill until slightly thickened.
Spread Cool Whip over bottom and up sides
of pie crust.	Stir strawberries into thickened gelatin and
gently spoon on top of Cool Whip mixture.	Chill at least 3 hours.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled sweet potatoes in pan of water until tender; drain.
When cool, peel and slice into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Slowly stir in cream.
Add salt, hot sauce, Worcestershire and sherry. Cook until thick.
Cool sauce.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, shrimp and crabmeat.
Pour into large casserole.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; set aside.

title: baked egg dish
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.

title: m&m pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Then stir in candies and peanut butter.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil the Jell-O, sugar and water.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese, baby food and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly. Chill bowl and beaters; beat milk until it thickens.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Top with ground or chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.
This recipe makes a lot, but it keeps well in refrigerator.

title: fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and evaporated milk.
Boil 8 minutes. Add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 6 x 14-inch dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool broth. Tear off pieces of chicken and put in buttered 3-quart oblong casserole or 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: strawberry-tomato preserves
directions: Boil for 20 minutes:
tomatoes, sugar and lemon juice.
Add strawberry jello.
Pour into hot jars immediately.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Pour Milnot into large mixing bowl and chill well; also chill mixer beaters.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add lemon juice and cool.
Let cream cheese soften, then mix in sugar and vanilla (by hand).
Add Jell-O (gradually) and mix well.
Whip Milnot until stiff and fold Jell-O mixture very gradually (by hand) until well mixed (gently).
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo together and press 2/3 of crumbs into 3 (9-inch) pie plates.
Put cheese-Jell-O mixture into plates.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and chill overnight if possible.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Form mixture into balls.
Dip in sugar; put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Blend Miracle Whip, sugar and cocoa with wooden spoon. Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Blend in first mixture.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: sunday chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Bake cornbread and cool.
Saute onion and celery.
Heat broth and soups together and pour over cornbread.
Add veggies.
Salt and pepper.
Pour half into 7 x 9-inch glass dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour remaining dressing over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheets. In large bowl, combine sugar, shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla, blend well. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, soda, pecans, dates and 1/3 cup of cherries, mix well. If desired, chill dough for easier handling. Drop by teaspoonfuls into crushed cereal, coat evenly. Form into one inch balls, place on cookie sheets, top with piece of cherry and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 60 cookies.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients; stir in. Blend.
Divide dough in half.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out dough.
Cut in shapes.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Cool and decorate. Makes 2 dozen.

title: half hour apple butter
directions: Bring to boil in heavy saucepan.
Cook 1/2 hour, stirring often.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain fruits well.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Stir well.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells (8-inch size).
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Set aside.
Cut chicken in strips.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in margarine, coat with crumb mixture and place in single layer in baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and pepper in a skillet until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour.
Mix in next 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and olives.
Spread evenly in 9-inch square pan.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to directions and spread over sausage.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; loosen edges.
Invert onto plate.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until soft ball stage.
Test in cold water.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla. Beat until cool.
Add nuts.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water and the egg.
Mix well.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Rub surface with Crisco.
Cover lightly and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep about 1 week.
When ready to use dough, punch down and roll out on floured board until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter or shape rolls as desired.
Brush with butter, fold over and place on ungreased baking sheet and allow to rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in hot oven, 425°, about 20 minutes.
Makes 24 Parker House rolls.

title: batter for corn dogs
directions: Beat batter very well.
Dip in cold hot dogs in this batter. Drop in hot fat for approximately 3 to 4 minutes.

title: chocolate pie(blender method)
directions: Blend in blender yolks, vanilla and milk.
Mix together cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add dry ingredients to blender.
Melt butter in saucepan and pour in blended mixture.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until bubbly and thickened (use a wide flat spatula to stir with).
Pour mixture into 9-inch baked shell.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and shape into a ball. Roll in nuts and chill until serving time.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly together the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and salt to shortening mixture.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Slightly beat egg whites until frothy with fork.
Dip balls into egg whites, then roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint in each cookie.
Bake about 12 to 13 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool. Fill centers with any color or flavor powdered sugar icing. Makes about 60 to 75 small cookies.
Great for showers or weddings.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat thoroughly in fat.
Add water and seasonings.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add celery, onions and cornstarch mixed with liquid. Add soy sauce, chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Stir and cook until thickened and meat tender.
Add mushrooms just before done.
Serve over rice.
Serves 18.

title: aunt mae's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler until all is smooth.
Add can of Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and pecans.
Stir well, put in 13 x 9 inch glass baking dish.
Set in refrigerator until almost firm. Cut into pieces and put back in refrigerator, let set and cut again.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over the ground beef in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add Cheddar cheese over soup, then add layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° until set, about 45 minutes. Top with marshmallows and cook until browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: spider sandwiches
directions: With a round cutter (a cup or glass works good), cut a circle from each bread slice.
Spread circles with peanut butter to make sandwiches.
Make 2 small indentations on top for eyes and use peanut butter as glue for the raisins.
Place sandwiches in a covered container and refrigerate.

title: elma's little bacon pizzas
directions: Drop all ingredients, except bread, in blender and chop thoroughly.
Cut crust off many slices of bread and arrange on cookie sheet.
Cut bread into small bite squares.
Spread each square with the blender mixture and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread(sugar free for diabetics)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine margarine, egg & almond extract.
Add to first mixture stirring until flour is moistened. Fold in mashed bananas.
Put in 9 inch well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate. Add egg, beating well.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 3/4 cup water, beating after each addition.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Arrange walnut halves over top.
Bake 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched.

title: choco-peanut ring cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugars gradually and beat thoroughly.
Beat in egg, then vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Form into 1 1/4-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheets; flatten slightly.
Press one peanut butter cup candy half in center of each cookie, peanut butter side up.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: "wurst" onion cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine liverwurst spread, 1 tablespoon sour cream, lemon juice and crumbled onions.
Unroll dough and cut into 4 rectangles.
Cut each rectangle into 6 equal pieces, then roll each piece into a ball.
Place 1 ball of dough in each of 24 gem-size (1 1/2-inch) ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough to evenly cover bottom and sides of muffin cups.
Fill each with 1 generous teaspoonful of liverwurst mixture, keeping level with edge of dough.
Top each with 1 teaspoon of sour cream and bake until crust is golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: homemade egg beaters(low calorie)
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Can be stored for 1 week.
Can be frozen.

title: super pumpkin cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan and flour clear glass pan.
Pour cake mix in bowl and then measure 1 cup out and set aside.
Use pastry blender to mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Press out in bottom of pan.
Grease fingers or a fork.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Combine all ingredients, except flour and butter, in mixer bowl; beat with electric mixer at low speed.
Add flour gradually, stirring with large spoon.
Place in greased bowl; brush lightly with oil. Refrigerate, covered.
Use as needed.
Roll on floured surface; cut into desired shapes.
Place in baking pans.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
May bake, freeze and reheat at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper.
Spread in casserole.
Add macaroni, tomato sauce, seasoning and water.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package (13 x 9-inch pan). Cool for 15 minutes.
Poke holes through cake. Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 minute. Spoon over warm cake.
Cool.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into topping. Spread over cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top. Chill overnight.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender; drain. Season to taste with salt and pepper; mash.
Combine remaining ingredients with squash and stir.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Pack in jars; grape leaves in bottom of jar.
Put cucumbers in a layer at a time.
Put a few green grapes in; put 3 tbsp salt. Fill with water.
Let set 3 days and drain off.
Rinse off lightly and put 3 tbsp salt.
Fill with water and let set a few days then put in freezer.
Take out and eat.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix eggs and milk.
Add salt, mustard and bread crumbs.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put the other 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: peas
directions: Place ingredients in a boiling pan and boil them.

title: never fail icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir until sugar begins to dissolve. Let come to a good boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well and spread.
Great when used on Hershey Bar Cake.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and milk.
Blend well.
Pat dough into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan on bottom and sides.
Place rhubarb in crust and pour with filling.

title: chocolate-berry layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Beat eggs and sugar in a medium bowl until thick and light colored. In a large bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add oil, buttermilk and vanilla to flour mixture, blend well. Fold in egg mixture. Pour into prepared pans and bake for 30 minutes. Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks. Spread preserves onto bottom layer, add top layer. Frost top with chocolate frosting.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in a crock or dishpan. Cover with 1/3 cup salt and water to cover.
Let soak overnight. Drain well.
Then bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Add drained zucchini and mix. Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together with electric beaters the cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle top with a few graham crackers and refrigerate.

title: fudge
directions: Melt all ingredients except nuts over hot water.
Beat mix until creamy; add nuts; pour into a wax paper lined pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Leave ends of paper long and you can lift all out after it has cooled.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Crush peanuts.
Mix all with a mixer.
Serve with apples.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, salt and pepper together.
Cook lasagna noodles per package instructions.
Drain and lay on waxed paper.
Mix together cheeses, eggs and basil.
Put thin layer of sauce in bottom of pan.
Layer lasagna noodles.
Top with spinach and cheese mixture. Keep layering and end layering with lasagna noodles.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening, then mix sugar and cocoa.
Add to melted shortening; stir until mixed good.
Add 2 eggs; add to other ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: green chili pie
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add tomatoes and soup and simmer a few minutes.
Layer meat, cheese and Doritos several times in a casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in a preheated oven to 325°.

title: poor man's crab imperial
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper.
Mix with crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Spread 3/4 bread mixture over.
Add rest of bread on top.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Spread undiluted soup over.
Spread grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: confectioners sugar icing
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa and water together.
Pour over sugar and blend; add vanilla.
If icing is too stiff, add very small amounts of milk to right consistency to spread.

title: apple surprise (cobbler)
directions: Fill pan 3/4 full with sliced apples.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add egg to mixture until it crumbles.
Spoon over top of apples, then add cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg over that. Pour over that 1/2 cup water.
Dot with butter.

title: corny garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Remove papery outer skin from garlic (do not peel or separate cloves).
Brush with oil.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until softened.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut top off garlic head, leaving the root end intact. Squeeze garlic into a large bowl; set aside.
Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and add to garlic.
Add the butter, sour cream, milk and parsley; mash.
Add the onions, corn, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: banana chocolate cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into graham cracker crust.
Mix instant pudding with evaporated milk, rather than regular milk.
Pour over sliced bananas; top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate until cold.
Tell everyone you worked all day making this pie from scratch.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Heat 1 cup syrup to boiling. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Cut ice cream and add to hot mixture.
Stir until melted.
Add almond extract. Chill until thickened and begins to mound.
Reserve a few peaches for garnishing.
Fold remaining peaches into mixture; pour into shell.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Cover top of filling with deep layer of whipped cream, almost to edge.
Top with peaches and fluff of cream in center.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients except parsley. Roll into a ball.
Then roll in parsley.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until slightly softened. Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except seeds.
Cover tightly and bake until broth has been absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Using fork, mix in sunflower seeds. Makes 6 servings.

title: russian dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a quart jar and shake well.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Serve with extra chili powder.

title: lillian's pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and margarine and press into 8 x 8-inch pan (or slightly larger).
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain off juice from beans.
Mix all ingredients together. Add enough mayonnaise to suit you.
Add salt and pepper.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and sugar over low heat.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
This recipe makes 2 pies and freezes well.

title: fish-vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Arrange fish in ungreased oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Rinse frozen peas under cold water to separate; drain.
Spoon peas, cucumber, celery and onion onto fish; sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and lemon juice.
Dot with margarine.
Cover; bake until fish flakes easily with fork, 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with lemon wedges if desired.

title: no cook lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk and sugar.
Add eggs last.
Beat well.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix ingredients well and put into casserole dish.

title: pimento-cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread; mix well.
Spread on 8 slices of bread.
Serve cold or butter outside of sandwiches and broil until cheese melts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn with crackers, chunk or shredded cheese, milk and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange frosting
directions: Mix with mixer margarine, orange rind and sugar until creamy. Add orange juice until spreadable.
Spread on Peanut Bars. Drizzle with Chocolate Icing.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together in 2 quart casserole.
Add beef and onion. Bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicago pizza dough
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast and salt. Mix well.
Add warm water and oil to flour mixture.
Blend at medium speed for approximately 3 minutes.
By hand, gradually stir in remaining flour to make a firm dough.
On floured surface, knead dough 3 to 5 minutes.
Place dough in a bowl and cover with plastic wrap and a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to the size of pizza pan.
Lightly oil pan and place dough on top of it.
Cover with towel and let rise for an additional 30 minutes.
Add your favorite toppings and bake at 425° until bottom of dough is brown (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: garden supper salad
directions: Core, rinse and thoroughly drain lettuce. Refrigerate in plastic bag or crisper.
Peel and slice carrots. Steam until just tender and cool. Cut pepper into chunks. Thinly slice green onions, cucumber and mushrooms.
Lightly steam pepper and onions until tender and crisp.
In a large bowl, combine steamed vegetables, cucumber and mushrooms.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Add artichokes to bowl.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Melt butter in small glass bowl in microwave oven for 45 to 60 seconds on High.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over peaches.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven for 7 to 8 minutes at High; rotate dish one-quarter turn.
Makes 8 servings.

title: florentine artichoke dip
directions: Drain spinach; press between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Pulse pieces of French bread in a food processor until coarse crumbs form.
Measure crumbs, and repeat procedure until you have 1 1/2 cups.
Combine spinach, artichoke hearts, and next 5 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 11-inch by 7-inch baking dish.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter; sprinkle over spinach mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Serve with assorted crackers or breadsticks. Yield:
4 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and put extra catsup on top of meat loaf to make a thick coating.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: milk frosting
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan, then add sugar and milk.
Boil gently, without stirring, for 13 minutes.
Beat until stiff enough to spread, then add flavoring and spread over cake.

title: brown rice chicken bake
directions: Combine rice, peas, chicken, mayonnaise, almonds, soy sauce and seasonings in bowl.
Transfer to 3-quart baking dish, coated with cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: crunchy coconut squares
directions: Stir almond flavoring into condensed milk in a small bowl. Cut each slice of bread into 4 squares and the 1/2 slice into 2 squares.
Dip each square into milk, removing excess dripping. Then dip in coconut, covering all sides and edges.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 18 squares.

title: marinated italian chicken breast
directions: Marinate chicken several hours or overnight with 1/2 bottle Italian dressing. Place breasts in casserole dish with the rest of Italian dressing. Add butter and water. Bake at 325° in oven until chicken is done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix together all ingredients. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Hollow out center of bread and pour dip into it.
Break up bread sticks, raw vegetables and more bread for dipping.

title: welsh froise
directions: Mix ingredients together, making a thin batter.
Pour like pancakes on a hot, greased frypan.
Add a few currants in the middle of batter while frying.
Brown on both sides.
Put on plate and spread with butter and sugar.
Stack like pancakes, then use a sharp knife and quarter them.

title: orange buttermilk shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on high speed until smooth. Pour into tall glasses.
Makes 2 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer water and bouillon cubes.
Cook carrots, celery, potatoes and onions 15 minutes.
Precook cauliflower and broccoli. Add vegetables and Velveeta cheese to water and bouillon; do not boil.

title: pickled sweet peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Remove tops and seeds.
Cut peppers into strips.
Cover strips with boiling water.
Let stand 2 minutes. Drain.
Pack peppers into hot sterilized jars.
Boil sugar and vinegar together 5 minutes.
Pour over peppers to fill jars. Seal.
Makes about 3 (8 ounce) jars.

title: indian spinach salad
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine vinegar, oil, chutney, sugar, salt, curry powder and mustard.
Cover and chill.
Place spinach in a large salad bowl with apple, raisins, peanuts and green onion.
Shake dressing; pour over salad and toss.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Combine and pour in freezing tray the following:
frozen strawberries, lemon juice and sugar.
Freeze until firm.
Toast walnuts for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Add to whipped cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread this mixture over frozen strawberries and freeze for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes clean and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Brush each slice with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until soft and light brown.

title: frozen bananas
directions: Will also need popsicle sticks and Ziploc baggies.

title: stuffed ham rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine spinach, stuffing and sour cream.
Spread 1/4 cup mixture down center of each ham slice. Roll up and place seam side down in single layer in greased 12 x 8 x 1 1/2 baking dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour and gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Add Cheddar cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Pour over ham. Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake in oven 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve hot with sauce spooned over rolls.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken on the bottom.
Top chicken with cheese. Combine soup and water. Spoon over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle with stuffing. Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: autumn tea loaf
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin and molasses.
Cream shortening, vanilla, orange rind and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add dry and liquid ingredients alternately, a little at a time.
Stir in walnuts. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put kraut undrained in a bowl and layer other ingredients. Boil together sugar and vinegar. When mixture is cool, pour over ingredients. Let stand in icebox 12 hours before serving.

title: tater tot hamburger casserole
directions: Place ground beef in a casserole dish. Layer remaining items in the order given. Mix soup and water together; pour over casserole. Top with Tater Tots. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: *For richer cake, butter may be used.

title: pasta fritters
directions: Coarsely chop spaghetti.
Thinly slice onions and shred zucchini.
Set aside.
In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil until very hot.
In a medium bowl, mix egg, flour, water, salt and pepper. Stir in spaghetti, zucchini and onions.
Drop 1/4 cup mixture into oil and flatten with spatula.
Cook until brown on one side, then turn.
Brown until golden.
Repeat until all mixture is gone. Makes 12 fritters.
Great as a side dish.

title: broccoli n' olive salad
directions: Combine
broccoli, olives, onion, eggs and water chestnuts. Toss
with
mayonnaise.
Serve
chilled in bowl or hollowed melon shell.

title: one egg chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: banana pudding
directions: Separate eggs; use yellows.
Mix yellows with sugar; add cornstarch and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas.
Place in layers.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and add the jello which is dissolved in the water.
Let set.
Serves 9.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices together and stir into first mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Wrap in foil when cool.
Keep in refrigerator or freeze.

title: blueberry cake or muffins
directions: Coat blueberries with a small amount of the flour.
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Makes either 1 dozen muffins or an 8-inch square cake.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix whole eggs, which have been beaten with the melted butter, buttermilk, brown sugar and blackberry jam.
Add flour which has been sifted with the cinnamon, allspice, soda and nutmeg.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 9-inch tube pan.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, 1 C. milk and 2 Tbsp. margarine. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread in waxed paper lined 8 inch square pan.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots thin.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain.
Add pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over carrots and pepper.
Let stand until cool.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
May be kept for several weeks.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour until fluffy. Add pineapple and pour into a well-greased casserole (8 x 8-inches). After tossing bread cubes in melted butter, add 3/4 of crumbs to pineapple mixture. Use rest as topping pressed slightly down. May add shredded cheese on top. Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Lay biscuits and roll together to form a 4 x 11-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Spread sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch thick sections.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until light brown.

title: fried ham with red eye gravy
directions: Cook ham slowly in heavy frying pan until evenly browned on both sides.
Sprinkle each side lightly with sugar during cooking. Remove ham and keep it warm.
Add coffee to pan; let it boil until gravy turns red.
Blend and pour over ham.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat oil. Add onion, green pepper and garlic and saute over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce, water, broth mix and seasonings and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix
yellow
cake
mix,
melted butter and 1 beaten egg. Pat in
bottom
of
9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil until browned.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until crisp-tender.

title: low-fat classic chicken noodle soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine the chicken, stock, carrots, celery, onions and oregano.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Lower the heat to medium and simmer 15 minutes or until the chicken is tender.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini, mixing well.
Stir in zucchini. Spread evenly in a lightly greased 13x9x2 inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Serve warm. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: pork, shrimp, ham fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Toss rice in oil until hot and golden.
Add scallions and meat.
Stir in last 5 ingredients until heated throughout.
Serves 12.

title: holiday party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of candies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate top with remaining candy. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Some cracking should occur.
Makes about 72 (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: shrimp and tortellini
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla to milk. Alternate with milk and dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan melt chips and margarine; stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large bowl beat cheese until fluffy; beat in condensed milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan; top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mash salmon in bowl; add eggs and 1/2 of crackers (crumbled). Mix onions into mixture with cheese and remainder of cracker crumbs.
Shape into patties and brown in hot oil for several minutes, turning often.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Peel, slice and arrange a layer of potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add layer of red beans.
Crumble layer of ground beef over beans.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion rings and cover with catsup.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large saucepan, combine water with butter and salt.
Heat over medium heat, until butter melts and water boils.
Turn heat low; add flour all at once and beat mixture thoroughly with a wooden spoon until it leaves the sides of the pan in a smooth compact ball.
Immediately remove pan from heat.
With a wooden spoon or portable mixer at medium speed, beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each egg.
When all eggs are blended, beat dough until very smooth and satiny.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix together first four ingredients, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Then add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add soups, cheese, broccoli and seasonings.
Add rice and pour into large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: meatza pie
directions: Place beef in 9-inch pie pan with garlic and crumbs.
Add milk.
Stir and spread evenly.
Add sauce or catsup and spread evenly.
Arrange mushrooms and then cheese on top of meat. Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts and begins to brown.
Cut in wedges.

title: home fries
directions: Cook potatoes (with skins on) in chicken broth until done. Cool in refrigerator for several hours.
Cut chilled potatoes in 1 1/4-inch chunks.

title: rich hot rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture; beat well by hand or mixer at low speed for 1 minute.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of bowl.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and satiny and no longer sticky, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; invert to grease top and cover and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; divide in half and shape as desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together until fluffy and put in graham cracker pie shell.

title: tammi's lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Drain and let cool.
Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add Prego; cook for about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Using a casserole dish, spread 1 spoon of sauce mixture across bottom of dish, then lay noodles side by side until bottom of dish is covered.
Lay 3 or 4 noodles in opposite direction in middle and each end.
Layer with Mozzarella cheese, meat and Parmesan cheese, then noodles until desired depth.
Put in oven and bake 20 minutes.

title: good luck bean soup
directions: Add salt to beans and peas; cover with water and soak overnight.
Rinse and put beans into 2 quarts of water.
Add ham or ham hocks and onion.
Boil slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: hermits(2 dozen)
directions: Mix sugar, oil, nutmeg, soda and cinnamon in a large bowl alternately with flour, milk and molasses.
Mix well.
Fold in raisins.
Spray pan with Pam.
Spread evenly over a 9 x 12-inch or a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes exactly. Cool, then cut into squares.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add other ingredients except sour cream.
Cool a few minutes.
Add sour cream.
Stir thoroughly to remove any lumps.
Congeal.

title: crabmeat and shrimp pistolettes
directions: Melt margarine, saute seasonings.
Add flour and milk.
Stir until smooth and add cheese, stir until melted.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and season to taste.
Scoop out pistolettes and fill like a boat.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake until hot at 350 degrees.

title: greek dressing
directions: Put all the ingredients in a jar and cover.
Shake thoroughly and chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: light as a cloud(custard pie)
directions: In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: baked fillet of flounder
directions: Place flounder in cold water; thaw only to separate pieces. Place on aluminum foil-lined pan.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Yields 3 servings.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and garlic with remaining salt.
Fold in potato dices.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice the potatoes and cook until done; drain.
Add milk to cover potatoes.
Add the mushroom soup and salt.
Put back on stove; bring to a boil.
If too thin, thicken with 1/4 cup milk and 2 teaspoons cornstarch.
If you don't like mushroom soup, add some Velveeta cheese.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Rinse off roast.
Rub all spices into roast.
Place roast in crock-pot.
Add enough water to just cover roast.
Cover and cook on high overnight.

title: italian hamburger pie
directions: Brown the beef and onions.
Combine all of the ingredients, except the cheese and biscuits.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle the mix with the grated cheese.
Halve 6 of the biscuits and arrange on the hot meat mixture.
(Leftover biscuits may be baked on a separate sheet.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Serves 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add beets and heat through.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Combine corn, milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 cup cheese; save remainder for topping.
Combine bread crumbs, melted butter and rest of cheese.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mixture will curdle.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Good side dish served with ham.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add butter and hot pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: cheesy pepperoni bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut five 1/8-inch thick slices from pepperoni; cut each slice into 8 wedges.
Set aside.
Cut remaining pepperoni into 1/4-inch cubes.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and oil in small bowl; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in cheese, chilies and cubed pepperoni.
Spoon batter into greased mini-muffin cups, filling each almost to top.
Top each muffin with 1 wedge of reserved pepperoni, pressing halfway into batter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a sauce pan, bring sugar and milk to a boil;
boil for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow creme; mix well. Quickly pour into a buttered 8-in. square pan; chill until set. Cut into squares. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potato for 1 hour at 400°.
Let cool.
Scoop pulp out in a bowl.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk gradually.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onion, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until heated.
Stir in sour cream and heat until cheese melts slightly.
Top with remaining onion, bacon and cheese.

title: doodle noodle
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips and brown in olive oil; drain. Pour water over steak.
Chop onion and add to steak.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Make gravy, following directions.
Pour gravy over steak.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix together and serve immediately.

title: company chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Put into pan.
Mix tomato soup and golden mushroom soup together with 2 soup cans of water.
Add mushrooms. Pour this mixture over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until chicken is done.

title: jalapeno and beer baked short ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Arrange short ribs in single layer in 2 large baking pans. Sprinkle onions around ribs.

Combine all remaining ingredients, except beer and cilantro, in large saucepan. Simmer over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Stir in beer. Pour mixture over ribs. Cover pans with foil and bake until meat is very tender, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: date nut roll
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage.
To this, add dates, nuts, oleo and vanilla.
Boil to a little harder stage. (Dropped into cold water, it forms a ball.)
Beat until creamy. Pour on wet towel (long); slice before firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and serve immediately.

title: mrs. u.s. moser's 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done when lightly touched.

title: crunch drops
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mustgo
directions: Cook ground beef until the pink is gone.
Drain very good. Layer the ground beef, carrots, onion, cabbage and potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir the 2 soups together and pour over the casserole.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.

title: chili
directions: Cook and drain ground beef/turkey. Add other ingredients in slow cooker. Cook about 5 hours or more.
Serve with grated Cheddar or Parmesan cheese.

title: new england chicken and wild rice(delicious)
directions: Place chicken, water, salt, onion and celery in pot and bring to boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Strain broth.
Refrigerate broth and chicken.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite-size pieces. Saute mushrooms in butter until light golden brown.
Use broth for cooking rice, following package directions for firm rice. Combine chicken, rice and mushrooms in 4-quart casserole.
Blend sour cream and undiluted soup.
Toss together with chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook breasts. Cut up into bite size pieces.
Crush chips and layer them in the bottom of a baking dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the following order:
chicken, onion, garlic, mushroom soup, tomatoes, chicken soup and grated cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake for 20 more minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk; mix well.
Store in bowl with tight fitting lid.
Batter will stay fresh for 6 weeks.
(We usually bake some immediately and save the remainder.)

title: lemon delight
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice, rind and egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat egg whites and whipped cream into cooled custard.
Pour into dish (which has layer of crumbs).
Then sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Freeze.
Take out a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Boil slowly, stirring often, to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Cool to lukewarm. Beat and add nuts.
Spread in greased pan.
Cut into squares.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add rest of ingredients and place in saucepan.
Cook until thick, then pour in pie crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add remaining ingredients in layers.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: fruit flavored gelatine(diabetic recipe)
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over water; heat over low heat or in microwave oven until water is hot and gelatine is dissolved.
Add drink mix and sweetener to hot gelatin mixture; stir until dissolved.
Pour into mold or dish; refrigerate until firm.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut up and peel eggplant night before.
Salt and layer so water drains out.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese and olive puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Wrap approximately 1 teaspoon of mix around each olive.
Arrange wrapped olives on cookie sheet, cover and freeze until firm.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: nutty ham and cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, pecans, green onions and garlic salt; spread on roll.
Layer ingredients in order listed.

title: happy home
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and blend well.
Sprinkle last ingredient on top.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix squash, egg, onion, salt, pepper and flour.
Add corn meal until this mixture looks like hush puppy dough.
Put small amount of oil or grease in a skillet, just enough to cover bottom.
Too much will make patties greasy.
Cook over medium heat until done on one side.
Turn over.
Cover until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
In a large saucepan, bring potatoes to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until tender; drain and let cool.
Peel and halve lengthwise.
In a large skillet, combine butter, salt, sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Stir over low heat until butter melts and sugar is dissolved, then boil, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add potato halves and pecans. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes basting often with syrup.
Serve potatoes with syrup and nuts spoon on them.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add peppers, beans, corn, chili powder, garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until done.
Spray bottom of casserole dish with Pam cooking spray. Crush chips along bottom of pan.
Add filling.
Spoon sour cream on top, then add cheese.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve over lettuce.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts in water with salt, onion and celery until done. Remove chicken from bone and return to juice. Add cream of chicken, mushroom, Velveeta cheese, black pepper, chili powder and Ro-Tel to mixture. Boil over low heat until cheese is melted. Pour over tostado chips and top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake in 350° oven until all the ingredients are done, about 45 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: lime punch
directions: 1 package Kool-Aid plus water makes 3 trays of ice cubes. Serves 25.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except oats in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir down 2 to 3 times.
Do not boil over 1 minute. Remove from heat, stir in oats.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet as quickly as possible or they will sit up in pan.

title: caramel squares
directions: Butter rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat candies and water in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently, until smooth.
Stir in cereal and nuts until completely coated. Press mixture in pan with buttered back of spoon.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pan and bake 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting into 16 to 20 pieces.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter; season with salt and parsley flakes.
Drain mushrooms and combine with noodles, soup and corn. Add meat mixture and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tiajuana hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic in frypan.
Remove excess grease.
Add tomato sauce, salt, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: banana bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in bananas and egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: cheddar egg bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef, bean and noodle skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet with cover, saute beef for about 5 minutes, stirring until meat loses its red color.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and basil.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat over low heat until it starts to bubble.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through.
Stir well.

title: instant chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Put 3 tablespoons in cup and pour in boiling water.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine well beaten egg, sugar and cooking oil.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add 3 cups self-rising flour.
Cover.
Let rise 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in baking pan and let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: cheese cake kuchen
directions: Combine butter, flour, 2/3 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Spread in bottom of greased and floured 11 x 7 x 3-inch pan.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Pour off 1/2 juice from pineapple.
Mix remaining juice, pineapple chunks and cheese together.
In another bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Stir sugar and flour mixture into pineapple cheese mixture and mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with a layer of crushed crackers.
Spoon melted butter on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish. Cover with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in hot fat until they bubble.
Drain.
Place a layer in a 3-quart casserole.
Top each tortilla with onion, cheese and meat that has been broken up, browned and drained. Continue until all tortillas are used.
Combine milk, soup and green chilies; pour over tortilla layer.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: orange sponge
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
When thickened, beat in rest of ingredients.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix bread, eggs and garlic in ground beef; roll into balls. Brown in pan.
In another pan brown the sausage then pour in 2 large cans tomato puree and 1/2 teaspoon garlic, parsley and oregano.
Then add the ground beef.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Gradually add flour and salt, mixing at low speed just until blended; stir in vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes clean.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.

title: cold pumpkin souffle
directions: Beat cream in a large bowl until soft peaks form.
Put half cup pumpkin pie filling into a small saucepan.
Stir in gelatin. Place on low heat stirring every 3 minutes until almost boiling. Remove from heat.
Add remaining pie mix in a large bowl.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup whipping cream.
Fold in remaining mixture until blended.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish or a 3-quart serving bowl.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip, chopped pistachio nuts and lightly sprinkle cinnamon.
Serves 12.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook molasses, syrup and vinegar to 270°
(hard crack).
Stir in butter and salt.
Pour slowly over popcorn and stir with wooden spoon to coat every kernel.
Butter hands and shape corn into balls.
Put on wax paper to harden.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch strips 1 1/2 to 2 inches long.
Melt margarine in skillet and cook onion and mushrooms until tender.
Remove and cook meat until browned. Reserving 1/3 cup of the broth.
Stir remaining broth, catsup, garlic and salt into the meat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved broth with flour, stir into meat.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: grandma olga's peanut cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix with oil and spices. Put crackers in a paper bag.
Toss crackers with 1/3 of the liquid at a time.
Store in an airtight container.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Cook over medium heat until hot.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Strain out spices.
Makes 11 cups or 22 half-cups.

title: great cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese
and
add finely chopped onions and beef. Roll into a
ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers. Chill overnight before serving.

title: kool-aid frozen dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour the canned milk and put in the freezer for about 20 minutes, or until crystals form around the edge of the bowl.
Whip until thick, then add the sugar.
When the sugar is dissolved, add the Kool-Aid.
Pour mixture on top of the crumbs, then sprinkle the remaining crumbs.

title: wonder cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, 3 tablespoons sugar and nuts. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until slightly brown at 350°.
Cool.
Mix soft cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix instant pudding in milk until thick.
Pour over second mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend powdered sugar, peanut butter, butter, vanilla and salt. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Heat the chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler until melted.
Dip the peanut butter balls and place them on wax paper or candy papers until chocolate hardens.

title: teriyaki meatballs(open house favorite)
directions: Combine beef, egg and bread crumbs.
Make meatballs.
Place in large flat pan and combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cook, uncovered, at 275° for 1 hour.
Serve warm in a chafing dish and serve with toothpicks.
Makes approximately 100.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain and pour cold water over top and drain again.
Add Salad Supreme, onion, pepper and all the Italian dressing.
Mix well and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day add tomato and cucumber and mix well.

title: garlic steak
directions: Trim excess fat off steaks.
Set oven to 400°.
Place steaks in baking pan (lined with foil).
Baste steaks in cooking oil, soy sauce and garlic powder combined.
Let stand 15 minutes.
With oven preheated, broil each side 10 minutes, or until desired browning is reached.
Serve with potatoes and vegetables on the side.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chili.
Add cubed cheese.
Warm in oven at 200° until cheese is melted.
Keep warm.
Use 1 bag of Fritos or Doritos for dipping.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over cooked loaf.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oats and raisins.
Beat eggs.
Add shortening and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: In a large covered saucepan, cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 5 minutes, drain.

title: coconut fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add rest of the ingredients and beat well. Drop on a greased cookie sheet or wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen candies.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in fridge until it chills. Roll into balls; bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Roll again in powdered sugar.
When finished, roll again.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and flour together until begins to thicken.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar by cooking in iron skillet until it caramelizes.
Stir this into the other mixture which has been cooked and kept warm.
It has to be good and hot when you pour the browned sugar in or it will lump.
Add butter last and cook a few minutes after adding; cool.
Pour into cooked pie crust and top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: In large bowl mash bananas.
Add butter and egg.
Beat well. In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Then add to banana mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Line muffin tin with baking cups.
Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until tops are golden brown.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt, fat, onions, water and sour cream.
Roll steak cubes in flour mix; brown in fat and add chopped onions.
Add water and mix well.
Gradually add sour cream.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar; then add vanilla.
Frost cake and enjoy!

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in covered container and marinate at least overnight.
Can be marinated longer but you must remove and knead well.

title: tarragon chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and dredge in flour; reserve remaining flour.
In large skillet heat butter, add chicken and brown on both sides.
Transfer to a heated platter. Add shallots to skillet and saute briefly.
Add wine.
Cook liquid over high heat until nearly evaporated.
Add reserved flour and make a thick paste.
Sprinkle with tarragon and stir in chicken broth.
Return chicken to skillet, cover and cook until tender, about 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, kernels, raisins and bacon.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over salad.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Grate Cracker Barrel and mix in cream cheese with a mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Mold into roll or ball and cover with nuts.

title: best brownies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a rapid boil and pour over the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda mixture.
Mix well the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and pour into other ingredients. Stir until lumps are out.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump in the crushed pineapple; spread.
Spread the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle the cake mix over top of fruit.
Dot with the butter.
(Add chopped nuts, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems so that you have a cavity.
Mix the stems in with the other ingredients and fill cavity evenly.
Place on a cookie sheet, open side up and bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes, or until sausage is thoroughly cooked. Serve immediately.

title: glogg nog
directions: Mix all together and serve sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and blend in shortening.
*In 1 cup measuring cup, beat egg; add a few drops of water.
Add vinegar; fill cup with water.
This equals 1 cup liquid.
Add liquid to flour and shortening mixture and mix.
Yields 6 single crusts.
Can be cut down to 1/2 recipe, equals 3 single crusts (still use the whole egg).
Rolls out great!

title: simple tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add heated mushroom soup, peas, onion and salt and pepper.
On occasion, I add pimento if I have them on hand.
Add tablespoon pimento, if desired.

title: brenda's chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
This is good served with whipped cream.

title: sheryl's swiss medley
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 1 cup of the onion (O&C).
Set aside for topping.
Combine all of the remaining ingredients. Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the reserved cheese and O&C onion rings and bake uncovered 5 minutes or until brown.
May be made ahead of time and frozen.
Thaw before cooking or increase cooking time.

title: hot ham and cheese pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
On wax paper press or roll each to form 7 x 5-inch rectangle.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice on each rectangle.
Fold dough in half over filling.
Press edges to seal.
Bake for 10 - 13 minutes.

title: hearty chicken 'n rice soup
directions: Combine broth, water, rice, celery and carrots.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until process cheese spread is melted.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.
Cooking time:
30 minutes.

title: crunchy sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef and onion together; drain well. Add mushrooms, water chestnuts and soy sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy do banana bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at low speed until until well blended.
Mix only until smooth.
Mix in nuts and cracker crumbs.
Pour into well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cover with foil the last 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and pour in a 9-inch square pan, then mix rest of ingredients and sprinkle over batter, then pour 1 1/2 cups water over this.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in greased 13 x 9 x 2 casserole. Cook sausage until brown, crumble and drain well. Spoon over croutons. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, milk or cream and salt. Pour over cheese. Cover and chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 8.

title: stuffed squash
directions: In a large bowl prepare Pepperidge Farm stuffing according to directions.
You may reduce the amount of butter though.
Add remaining ingredients.
Halve a butternut squash lengthwise.
Carve out center and spoon stuffing in.
Place squash in pan of water while baking.
Bake for 1 hour or so at 350°.
This is very good for Thanksgiving.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add onions, clams, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Thin to desired consistency with reserved clam juice.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and milk together.
Add cake mix and Jell-O already mixed together dry.
Add frozen strawberries, coconut and pecans.
Bake in well-greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° until it tests done.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind together tomatoes
and
onions.
Add
salt; cover with water.
Let stand
10 minutes; drain well.
Grind peppers and cucumbers and add.
Add remaining ingredients and boil all together for 15 minutes.
Put
in jars and seal.
Place in hot water bath, just to boiling point and turn off burners.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in pieces.
Cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Season with salt and pepper, dash of celery salt and garlic salt.
When tender, drain well in same container.
Add the butter in small pieces.
Put in hot potatoes and mash well. Stir in sour cream.
Place in casserole dish.
Spread with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and started to brown.

title: chocolate morsels
directions: Melt chocolate; add peanuts, marshmallows and Rice Krispies. Drop on wax paper.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Place shell in 9-inch pie pan.
Peel apples and slice really thin; place in shell.
Pour Equal over apples. Cut butter in thin squares and place over apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples. Cover with top shell.
Make slits in the top shell.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and cut up.
Boil sugar and water, then whip in the mayonnaise.
Mix in onion, carrots, celery, peppers and salt. Pour over potatoes and stir.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cook as directed on package.
Cool on cake racks.
When cool, split the two layers with a double strand of sewing thread.
Ice with split sides up.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl and set aside.
In saucepan, bring butter, sugar and water just to a boil. Remove from heat and add 6 ounces chocolate chip morsels and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Place chocolate mixture into a mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg. Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate chip morsels and the chopped almonds.
Spread into a 9-inch square baking pan and bake for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: vanilla pudding salad
directions: Mix the pudding and buttermilk.
Add the remaining ingredients. Before serving, add 1/4 package of fudge striped cookies, crushed.
(Can be made without the cookies.)

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir until liquid disappears and nuts are coated.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 225°.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Add ingredients to cooked broccoli.
Mix and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Beat avocados, onion, pepper, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Fruit-Fresh until creamy.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: apple chutney(sauce)
directions: Soak regular raisins in wine for an hour or so.
Drain and set aside.
Combine apples, sugar, margarine, drained wine, lemon juice, nutmeg and cinnamon in a large saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes until thickened.
Stir in raisins and cook 1 more minute until heated through.
Serve with pork, chicken, turkey or ham.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash 1 cup wild rice thoroughly and place in a large heavy saucepan filled with 3 cups boiling water and salted to taste. Reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook rice 50 to 60 minutes or until rice kernels puff open. Uncover and fluff rice with a table fork.
Simmer an additional 5 minutes.
Drain off any excess liquid and proceed with recipe.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut and wash wings and discard tips.

title: fried corn
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Cut off the cobb and add salt, sugar, bacon fat and water.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes or until corn is tender.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburg, onion, garlic salt and 1 tablespoon pepper until done.
Drain off fat.
Boil potatoes; drain.
Mash with milk, 1/2 stick butter, salt and 1 tablespoon pepper.
Place ground hamburger on bottom of baking pan, 9 x 11 x 3-inch.
Add layer of creamed corn and layer of drained kernel corn.
Add top layer of potatoes evenly over the top.
Place 2 pats of butter on top of the potatoes and bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: peanut butter-banana-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper cups. Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and baking powder. Whisk together milk, peanut butter, banana, egg, oil and vanilla; add to dry ingredients mixing until just moistened.
Fill prepared cups 3/4 full.

title: pumpkin bread(fat-free)
directions: With electric mixer, blend water and honey.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in pumpkin.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients. Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in walnuts. Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely. Yields 2 loaves.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and cocoa. Stir in milk and melted shortening. Blend in chopped nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour oven entire batter the hot water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Invert squares of pudding on plates. Dip sauce from pan over each. Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: italian pepper steak
directions: *Butcher will slice it free for you.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Use Bundt pan.

title: jalapeno cheese grits(servings:  8)
directions: Add grits to boiling water and boil until very thick.
Combine margarine and cheese until melted.
Add beaten eggs and stir.
Add green chilies.
Pour into greased casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 250° until thick.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not heat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread frosting between layers and top and sides of cake.
Put other cup of pecans on top.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add the other ingredients and simmer for about 1/2 hour.

title: orange drop donuts
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add orange juice, corn oil, grated rind and eggs.
Beat well.
Drop from a teaspoon in deep hot vegetable oil and fry until well browned.
Drain on absorbent paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: jean terry's batter for onion rings, eggplant or squash
directions: Beat egg.
Add shortening, water and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add.
This batter will thicken in just a few minutes.
Slice your onions; dip in batter. Fry in hot, deep fat.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with flour and vanilla. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in cold oven to start and place foil over pan for 1/2 hour, then remove foil and bake the other 30 minutes.
Bake at 325°.
Total baking time is 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a large nonaluminum kettle. Bring to a boil.
Reduce
heat.
Simmer
uncovered
to
40 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Pack into hot sterilized jars leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Seal; cool completely.

title: aladdin pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter; add egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to sugar and egg mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: ox tails
directions: Brown meat in fat in 5-quart Dutch oven; add onions, salt, bouillon cubes and spice bag, which consists of the peppercorns, bay leaf, parsley and clove of garlic.
Add boiling water to cover. Place celery and cabbage on meat; cook over low heat on range or in a 350° oven for 4 hours, adding water as needed.
Cool slightly and refrigerate, covered, overnight after removing spice bag.
Pick fat from top before reheating.
Strain liquid for soup.
Serve meat with vegetables.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Fill pie shell with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss cheese with Worcestershire sauce; sprinkle atop pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Trim with pickle slices, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 minutes.

title: soft-batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla together in a large bowl.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, instant pudding mix, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Fold in chips and nuts.
By rounded tablespoon for large cookies or teaspoon for small cookies, drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 minutes on cookie sheet, then remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Store, lying flat, and if stacking in container, place sheet of waxed paper between stacked layers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed, less 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Put into casserole.
