Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Line flat 13 x 9 casserole with broccoli, cooked al dente. Add layer of cooked chicken (boned); pour on top the soup, mayo and curry mixture. Top with cheese and crumbs. Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee ice cream pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter together with beater.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour ingredients into a graham cracker crust.
Top with chopped walnuts and freeze 3 to 4 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In saucepan, saute mushrooms and onions in butter or margarine.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
In double boiler, heat milk and light cream to warm, but not boiling.
Add mushrooms and onions and stir constantly.
Add sharp cheese, Tabasco sauce, soy sauce, salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate. Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut 1\2 inch from tip of each chicken wing; Seperate at joint. Place chicken in ungreased baking dish, 13 1\2x8.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate, turning chicken occasionally, at least 1 hour.

Heat oven to 375°. Remove chicken from baking dish, reserving sauce. Place chicken on rack in auminum foil lined broiler pan. Bake for 30 min. Brush with remaining sauce. Turn chicken, brushing occasionally with sauce, until chicken is glazed, 30-40 min.

title: jim's salmon patties
directions: Empty salmon in bowl.
Remove soft bone and dark skin.
Add beaten egg, onion, celery, crackers, salt and pepper; mix well. Form into patties.
Place in skillet with 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine.
Brown about 10 minutes on each side.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and pumpkin.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves. Add beaten eggs and cheese.
Separate dinner rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides.
Spread with mustard.
Add zucchini.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 6 servings.
Best second day.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat. Heat to boiling. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts. Stir 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows melt. Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in coconut, dates and nuts.
Roll into walnut size balls; place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: *pita dough
directions: Mix flour, water and salt until soft.
Knead for 10 minutes until it is very smooth, then cover for 10 minutes.

title: hamburg crumble
directions: Fry hamburg in small pieces and crumble.
Fry bacon and crumble. Place hot crumbled hamburg and bacon in bowl. Sprinkle on top: Cheddar, onion and olives. This can be served over rice, noodles or potatoes.
Serves 2.

title: pennsylvania dutch rivel soup
directions: Combine flour, salt and beaten egg.
Mix together with finger until crumbly. Drop mixture into boiling broth.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Rivels will look like boiled rice when cooked.

title: easy bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran with sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking soda and stir.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Spray small muffin pan with Pam.
Place mixture in muffin pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hearty chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup with skim milk, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: In a medium bowl, sift dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat wet ingredients until well combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 8 x 8 inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies(children grab these cookies as soon as they come out of the
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking soda into a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the peanut butter, shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add the dry ingredients a little at a time; mix well.
Mix in eggs and milk, then chill dough in refrigerator for 10 minutes. Make round balls and drop onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Mash with a fork and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: grape ice cream soda
directions: Put ice cream into tall glass.
Fill with chilled grape soda and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cauliflower dilly
directions: Cook flowerets in boiling water until tender (or steam). Don't overcook.
Pour into casserole.
(I put minced garlic into melted butter and pour over cauliflower.)
Shake on dill weed; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle Cheez Whiz over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swedish glug(hot holiday punch)
directions: Heat and simmer for at least one
hour.
Do not boil.
May also add walnuts.

title: spicy sausage and rice
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet; cook until done.
Drain on paper towels.
Discard pan drippings.
Return sausage to skillet.
Stir in rice and cook until rice is golden, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: an rv recipe
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Stir in hominy.
Heat, then stir in cheese.
Very tasty.
Serve with garlic bread and a salad, or slice tomatoes you have.
Maybe add a good cookie.

title: chicken breasts with almond sauce
directions: Boil 5 chicken breast halves in salted water.
Remove skin and bones and cut breast into large chunks.
Place in casserole. Layer of sauce, layer of chicken, layer of sauce and put crushed potato chips on top.

title: baked swiss chicken
directions: Place 1 slice of Swiss cheese over chicken breast or other parts.
Pour soup over all.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and press down into soup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter or oleo. Into the melted butter, stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in
a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour the fruit pie filling over.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Rinse off ice glaze.
Mix ingredients and spoon onto chicken breasts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wrap each hot dog half with bacon strip.
Fasten with toothpick.
Layer in crock-pot, sprinkling each layer with a thin layer of brown sugar.
Repeat layers until hot dogs run out.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours, stirring gently with wooden spoon every 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bowl; put in microwave on Full power for 3 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Put back and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and margarine and cook for 1 1/2 minutes. Add soda.
Mix and pour in greased cookie sheet.
Cook in 1-quart measuring cup.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into heavy skillet.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: crab meat and shrimp casserole
directions: Chop the green pepper, onion and celery in small pieces.
Mix ingredients lightly together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a shallow 2-inch deep casserole (fresh parsley may be sprinkled on top or added to contents as desired).

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening; saute meat (either pork chops or hamburg) until brown.
Remove meat.
Saute onions and peppers; add remaining ingredients and arrange meat on top.
When steaming freely, cover and cook on low 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Saute the onion and bell pepper in the margarine until clear. Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Stir and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: pastor's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Combine all ingredients and toss.
Add croutons and serve with Club crackers along with your favorite beverage.
Serves 8 to 12 people generously.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Set 1/2 cup of mixture aside.
To the remaining mixture, add the next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour first mixture into pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all together except oil.
Grease the frying pan or griddle and heat to medium-high.
Drop the mixture by tablespoonfuls in the pan and brown on both sides.
Serve warm.
This makes enough for 6.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a 3-quart bowl.
Add milk and butter; do not stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, then stir well.
Add nuts and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered dish.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a large container that will seal (omit bacon).
Seal tight and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: corn cakes
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl
and beat with electric mixer 1 1/2 to 2 minutes at top speed. If mixed by hand, beat eggs before adding. Batter will be thin. Cook on hot griddle that is generously greased with bacon grease.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bread in the bottom.
Cook sausage and drain.
Place over bread.
Layer cheese over sausage, then mushrooms.
Mix milk and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over all.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vidalia sweet onion bake
directions: Cook
onions
in
margarine.
Boil
rice in water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix well with onions, cheese and cream.
Bake in greased casserole at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves approximately 8.

title: graham candy
directions: Combine
the
sugar, oleo and milk; boil three minutes. Remove from heat and add the graham crackers (this is about 20 crackers, crushed), coconut and marshmallows.
Stir until the marshmallows melt
and pour into a large pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Stir soup until creamy; add milk, cheese, onion, uncooked macaroni and dried beef.
Fold in eggs and put all in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours, or overnight. Bake, uncovered, in 350°
oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Beat the eggs with a mixer until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
May brown in skillet as small patties to serve with spaghetti sauce or form into balls, place in baking dish, cover with mushroom or tomato gravy and bake.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate bread sticks. Lay pepperoni slices on 1/2 of each bread stick. Fold other 1/2 of bread on top and twist. Place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with seasonings. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Serve with pizza sauce.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and onions together.
Blend egg and buttermilk, then stir into dry ingredients.
Allow batter to sit 1/2 hour.
Drop into hot oil (375°) by tablespoon.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 200° oven until served.

title: lovers delight cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, egg yolks and flour. Chill. Roll very thin and cut into circles. Put a teaspoon of egg whites on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts. Bake until the edges turn a light brown at 350.

title: colonial seed cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine poppy seed and milk.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Grease and flour a standard size loaf pan. Combine with seed and milk mixture the eggs (at room temperature) softened butter, sugar and vanilla.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine shortening and flour mixtures together.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch or 1/2-inch thick.
May have to add more flour when rolling out dough.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal jelly bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, sugar, salt and shortening until well blended.
Put 1/2 of mixture into a greased
9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread jam evenly over mixture, not to get too close to edges of pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over jam and lightly flatten with fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Cook meat with taco seasoning.
When done, drain well.
Line dish with chips.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat pineapple juice and cornstarch in saucepan over medium heat until thickened.
Refrigerate until cooled.
In salad dish, mix cooled thickening with pineapple.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: recipe for slaw that can be frozen(this is a super slaw recipe.  you can even freeze it!)
directions: In a bowl, mix cabbage, onion, green pepper, carrot and salt. Let stand one hour.
In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients and let boil 2 minutes.
Let cool, then add to cabbage mixture.
Stir well and eat; or freeze in plastic containers for later.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in bottom of Pyrex dish; sprinkle cinnamon.
Mix sugar, sifted flour, salt and baking powder together; add egg and mix.
Place over apples; add small amount of butter and bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream sugar and margarine. Add milk, egg, 2/3 cup flour and all other remaining ingredients, except blueberries. Mix in remaining flour. Fold in blueberries. Fill cups 2/3 full and bake for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put the dry milk, peanut butter and honey into a bowl and mix well.
Cool mixture in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Roll small amounts of mixture into balls.
Put into covered container and store in refrigerator.
Makes several dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar & cinnamon. Quarter each biscuit & roll in sugar mixture. Place in bundt pan. Sprinkle left over sugar mixture on top, then pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. (Pull off pieces when eating.)

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients and make rolls, put in foil, with shiny side in, roll tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Place rolls on rack over cookie sheet, punch holes in bottom of foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.
Add apples and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla. Beat only until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
For glass pan, bake at 325°.

title: zucchini cake or zucchini muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in 13 x 9-inch casserole in order given.
Mayonnaise and Sweet 'N Low should be combined before layering.

title: spinach pudding
directions: Drain spinach well.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place pecans and coconut in bottom of greased oblong pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Pour over coconut and pecans. Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar, spoon over cake mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until test done.

title: shrimp dip (ball)
directions: Blend, form into a ball and refrigerate.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Beat in oil, eggs
and plums.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake
at
for
hour.
Let
cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and sugar in 2 cups water until cranberries pop; remove from heat and let cool.
Dissolve gelatine in the 1/2 cup water and cook until well blended; remove from heat and cool.

title: cerbone's summer punch
directions: Mix grape juice, pineapple juice and lemon (or lime) juice together. Add ginger ale and grape juice cubes just before serving. Serves 15 to 20.

title: snickerdoodle cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to butter mixture with the milk.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Test for doneness with toothpick, for the top is crusty and can't be touched for doneness as a regular cake can.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Cook applesauce in crock pot 10 hours.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Put in jars and seal.

title: orange ginger pork roast
directions: For marinade, stir together the first six ingredients and set aside.
Trim fat from pork; slice into 1-inch thick slices.
Place in storage container with marinade.
Cover and put in the refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Place on rack of broiler pan.
Roast in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once and brushing often with marinade.

title: 1-2-3 fruit dressing
directions: Mix sugar, egg, juice of lemon and lime and juice and grated peel of orange.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: eggplant and cheese
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Slice eggplant in 1-inch slices.
Salt eggplant and let stand 1 hour, then rinse.
Flour eggplant slices and fry until done.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir sugar and flour together and place in cooking dish. Add milk and stir until relatively smooth. Add peaches, including juice.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, green beans, corn, onion, celery and pimentos.
In a saucepan combine remaining ingredients. Heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over the vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 10-12 servings.

title: mom's vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown soup bone and stew beef in deep pot.
Cover with water. Simmer with onion and celery for at least 2 hours, keeping covered with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Half hour before eating, add potatoes and carrots, or any other vegetables you may have.

title: easy cherry chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, drop by rounded spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: stuffed won tons
directions: Prepare the hamburger meat and soya sauce by mixing them together.
Set aside.
Use water in a small bowl to wet each won ton.
Work with one won ton and about one teaspoon of hamburger mixture.
Wet won ton around the edges.
The won ton is square. Place the teaspoon of hamburger mixture in the middle; fold won ton so that it is now a triangle.
Pinch the sides together.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake in oven from 5 to 10 minutes.
Check by cutting open one of the won tons to make sure the hamburger is done.

title: southwestern steak
directions: Combine lime juice, steak sauce, salsa, oil, garlic and pepper in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Place steak in a plastic bag or marinating container; add cooled marinade, turning to coat.
Close bag or container and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 8 hours, preferably overnight. Remove steak from marinade and discard marinade.
Place steak on medium heat grill.
Grill steak 12 to 14 minutes for rare to medium, turning once.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook and drain squash; combine all ingredients except egg. Add egg, mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cow patty cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo, milk and vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° until bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add chicken stock and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Slowly add soup and cheese.

title: tortilla soup
directions: *Use white flour tortillas made of unleavened dough.

title: microwave shrimp creole
directions: Place butter, onions, green pepper and garlic in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave for about 3 minutes on High or until vegetables are partly cooked.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 5 minutes on reheat (80% power).
Stir, recover and continue cooking for 7 to 11 minutes on reheat (80% power).
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over hot rice.

title: vigdas cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the margarine, sugars and egg. Add remaining ingredients; stir by hand to blend, not beat mixture.
Place teaspoon size drops on an ungreased cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes a big batch.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Stir in 1 cup crumbs with the eggs. Stir 1/4 cup melted butter in the other 1/4 cup crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Stir in grated cheese, salt and pepper into asparagus.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° until set and brown (35 minutes).
Put casserole in a pan of water to bake.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients well.
The batter will not be smooth like a cake batter.
Pour into a greased 9x9x2 pan or round pan. Smooth batter evenly over pan.
Bake 18-20 minutes at 350 degrees. Let cake stand for 20 minutes.

title: beer batter
directions: Beat well all ingredients.
Can use with fish, chicken, shrimp, etc.
Deep fry.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Knead like dough and keep mixing until thoroughly mixed.
Shape into small balls and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in a small saucepan; drain fruits and arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over it and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Refrigerate until ready to use; then heat until warm.
Always prepare at least 1 day ahead of time.

title: braised chicken with sour cream
directions: Rub chicken with lemon juice.
Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter.
Place in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and cover with sour cream.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: peanut brittle(church recipe)
directions: In a glass, put soda, butter and salt.
Set aside until later. Put sugar, Karo and water in a 3-quart pot.
Cook until syrup spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until syrup turns caramel in color.
Remove from heat.
Add soda mixture and stir.
Pour quickly on foil and spread.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add enough water to cornstarch to make runny.
Blend cornstarch into egg mixture.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 1 hour and reheat to serve.
Add a scoop of vanilla ice cream and yum yum.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a skillet over moderate heat, cook sausage until brown on all sides.
Remove and slice sausage. Combine sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and sausage.
Place 1/2 of noodles in bottom of a 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Spread half of sauce mix over noodles and remaining noodles and spread cottage cheese evenly over noodles.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, butter, sugar and milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° in preheated oven.
When cake comes out of the oven, punch holes in cake with a knife and pour cream of coconut over cake while it is still hot.
Let cool, then ice.

title: gussie's corn bread
directions: Line pan with fat.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Heat pan of fat; add corn bread and cook in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Rinse, squeeze and drain.
Combine all ingredients and chill for 3 hours.
Pour into hollowed out loaf of bread.
Cut bread removed from loaf into bite-size pieces for dipping.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Place in large bowl with lid and refrigerate.
Each day mix well and knead for 3 days.
On fourth day make into 3 or 4 rolls.
Bake on broiler pan for 8 hours at 180°.
Turn every hour. Can be frozen or used as needed.
As a variation, we use 2 1/2 pounds hamburger and 2 1/2 pounds deer burger.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil, peanut butter and eggs. Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows begin to puff. Cool cake 15 minutes.
Drop frosting by spoonfuls onto warm cake. Spread gently.
Cool before serving.

title: banana split pudding
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers and 1 stick melted margarine. Press in pan.
Set aside.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil
chicken.
Cool
and
debone,
saving broth.
Saute peppers, onion and celery until tender, then add 2 cups chicken broth, tomato sauce and chicken.
Then add cooked spaghetti and other
ingredients
and cook 10 minutes, then add cheeses until melted.
Cooks well in crock-pot.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.

title: fried rice
directions: Lightly brown ham in skillet.
Add rice and vegetables; stir and warm over medium heat.
Scramble eggs in separate pan.
Chop and add to rice mixture.
Add soy sauce to taste and garnish with chopped onions before serving.

title: midnight mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased and floured 1-layer cake pan or double the recipe and use an appropriate pan. Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean.
Cake should be moist; test one layer after 25 minutes.

title: chiperoo bars
directions: Melt oleo and stir in brown sugar.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients. Pour in sugar mixture and add eggs, one at a time. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: tomato-shrimp salad
directions: Heat stewed tomatoes.
Add lemon Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve and let set until thick.
Add mayonnaise, celery, bell pepper, green onions and shrimp.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: my grandmother's "date oatmeal bars"
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 3 minutes, then allow to cool. Mix last 6 dry ingredients as for pie crust.
Spread 1/2 of the crust mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan and press until firm.
Cover with date filling, then pat remaining crust on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
When cool, cut into squares and watch them disappear!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add rest. Mix and bake at 375° to 400° until done.

title: bj's world class chili
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon to paper towel.
Brown onion slices in bacon grease until tender.	Remove onions.	Brown ground beef in same skillet.
Drain.
Crumble bacon.
Combine all ingredients into large casserole dish.
Stir well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 325° oven for one and one half hours.
Bake uncovered for thick chili; cover casserole for soupy chili.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to
Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend flour and salt. Stir in.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white.
Roll in nuts, if desired.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Press thumb gently into centers.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool. Fill centers with jelly or icing.

title: barbecued tuna
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan raisin muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in pecans and raisins; beat together egg and milk.
Add all at once to dry ingredients. Stir lightly to dampen dry ingredients.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat milk with beaters.
Add well beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer can and finish filling can with pasteurized milk.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend all the ingredients with enough no-fat salad dressing to moisten.
Makes about 3 cups.
Serving is 1/4 cup with 32 calories and 0.5 grams of fat.

title: play dough
directions: Boil water, salt and oil.
Add flour and alum, knead.
Makes white play dough.
If want color, add food coloring to oil first and mix well, then follow recipe.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Make marble cake mix and jello according to instructions on boxes.
When cake cools, poke holes with a toothpick.
Pour jello over the top.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then roll in little balls (walnut-size), then in top of double boiler mix chocolate chips and wax.
Stir until melted.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate, then put on wire rack to drip excess chocolate off.

title: barbados chicken in orange sauce
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken in flour mixture and fry in large pot in oil.
Do not deep fry.
Use only enough oil so chicken does not stick.
Remove chicken when it is well browned.

title: tofu loaf(vegetarian)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1-quart mixing bowl, mash tofu into small fine pieces with a fork or your hands.
Add the other ingredients with the tofu and blend together thoroughly.
If mixture looks too moist, you can add a little more oatmeal.
Put in loaf pan, pat down firmly and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all of the rest of the ingredients together and pour into dish.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup very warm water, stir to dissolve.
Add yeast and let set.
Scald milk, add Crisco, sugar, salt and water.
When warm add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well, add yeast mixture and beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft, pliable dough.
Knead well until not sticky. Grease sides and bottom of large bowl, turn dough in bowl to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Break into rolls and let rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Butter tops when done.

title: wasselman
directions: Stick whole cloves all over an orange.
Combine all the ingredients into your crockpot. Traditionally wine is added, but if you'd like it to be non-alcoholic fill crockpot to 3/4 full with apple or grape juice. Cook on high one hour.
Simmer on low 4 to 8 hours.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Spread cream cheese on bread.
Place a slice of zucchini on top; sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Makes a nice snack or appetizer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine soups.
Do not dilute.
Add rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Add melted butter to top of chicken.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
The last 30 to 45 minutes, uncover so chicken can be browned.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; mix in eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Add chocolate and nutmeats.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with waxed paper.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon; cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour; stir until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to hot vegetables, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Add processed cheese spread; stir until melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix into patties.
Flour and brown in oil one side more to hold in juice.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 can undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: girl scout hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/4 cup mix to one cup hot water.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown
hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Can also add sausage, mushrooms and more spices to taste.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour water over dates and raisins.
Melt butter.
Stir in eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and soda alternately with dates, raisins and nuts.
Fill greased 1-pound coffee cans 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 9 (1-pound) cans.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Note:
Toasted and shredded almonds may be used in place of mushrooms.
If so, let them be the last touch before serving.

title: cottage cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Mix jellos in boiling water; let cool but not set.
Add other ingredients well and mold.
Serves 6.

title: mexicali soup
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 teaspoon chili powder, salt and pepper. Shape into 12 meat balls.
Brown meat balls in butter and onions. Add soup and remaining chili powder. Fill can with water and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: banana bonanza cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Blend in 3 eggs.
Add bananas, mixing well.
Combine in separate bowl the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In large saucepan, cook ham and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Add garlic powder, tomato sauce, beef broth, 1 cup water, rice, bay leaf, sugar, thyme, chili powder and pepper.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.

title: shaggy dogs
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate bars over low heat.
Stir in milk to make thin syrup.
Put coconut in shallow dish.
Using a toothpick, dip marshmallows in chocolate syrup mixture and roll in coconut.
Cool on wax paper.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken for about 1 hour, skimming the top as needed. Remove and set aside to cool.
Break spaghetti; drop into chicken stock.
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, saute the onion and bell pepper in the Ro-Tel tomatoes.
When sauteed, add cheese and melt.
Debone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Save the stock!
Drain spaghetti.
Return spaghetti and chicken to pot; add cheese mixture.
Stir.
Add stock as needed for moisture.

title: rigatoni with carbonara sauce
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Meanwhile, cook bacon in oil until crisp.
Add wine.
Cook and stir until it has evaporated.
After draining macaroni, return to hot saucepan.
Mix remaining ingredients, including hot bacon fat.
Because this mixture will attach itself to the macaroni and be cooked by the heat of the pot and macaroni.
If eggs are not thoroughly cooked, stir over low heat for an additional minute.

title: 24-hour chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand overnight.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato - sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly and drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and vanilla. Add the chips and nuts. Stir in the flour.
Use a teaspoon and put on ungreased baking pan.
Press with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: flounder in wine
directions: Place
fillets	in a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle
with
teaspoon salt and pepper.
Arrange tomatoes on	top;
sprinkle	with
salt.
Carefully pour wine over
all; sprinkle with basil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle
with cheese
and
bake for 5 or 10 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serves 5.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add pineapple chunks with syrup to saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add butter or margarine, lemon juice and beets.
Cook over medium-high heat about 5 minutes or until heated through.

title: spinach appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes for easier handling.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and put in freezer about 20 minutes.
Can be kept in plastic bag or freezer until needed or bake at 350° for 20 minutes to use now.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
In small pan, put oleo, water, Crisco and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix soda and buttermilk.
Add buttermilk mixture and vanilla to ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan, about 11 x 15-inches.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
When cake has been baking 15 minutes, start to prepare icing.
Serves 20.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well. Shape into small balls. Chill. Melt the chocolate chips and butter in small pan.
Dip balls in mixture. Cool on wax paper.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: golden punch
directions: Prepare orange juice and lemonade according to directions on can. Add apricot nectar and pineapple juice; chill well.
To serve, stir in carbonated beverage and pour over ice.
Yields 1 gallon.
Good at Christmas!

title: ugly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make up the box of yellow cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour cake into a glass 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar well in a bowl. Then spoon the powdered sugar and cream cheese mixture on top of the raw cake.
Let this bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let it cool before cutting.

title: no sugar banana bread(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream margarine.
Add eggs, bananas and salt and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Add sour milk and lemon juice, mixing well. Pour into greased and floured bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole supreme
directions: Cut cabbage into pieces; boil until tender and drain.
Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp; drain and set aside.
Pour bacon grease into container (keep).
Wipe pan with cloth or paper towel.
Pour 2 or 3 tablespoons grease back into pan and add 1/3 of bread crumbs.
Turn crumbs until toasted; repeat with the rest of crumbs.

title: amish (sauerkraut) salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Then add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Refrigerate for 5 days.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Add potatoes.
Sprinkle with onion flakes and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 425° in covered dish until tender.
Remove cover and return to oven until brown.

title: red hot punch
directions: Put all ingredients in pot and boil.
Wonderful on a cold winter night.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter and peanut butter; combine and form into balls.
Mix chocolate and paraffin in double boiler and keep hot while dipping balls in chocolate and paraffin. Yields about 150 servings.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries; cut apples to remove core.
Peel the oranges and remove seed.
Grind or use food chopper to mix all ingredients.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Heat 1 cup juice to boiling point. Pour over lime jello and stir until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, melted butter and milk.
Mix well and add to dry ingredients with nuts and coconut.
Put in pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Butterfly shrimp leaving shell intact.
Marinate shrimp for 1 hour using above ingredients.
Turn once.
Grill shrimp for 3 to 4 minutes.
Brush with reserved marinade and cook 2 minutes more or until done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add 1/2 cup lemon juice and stir.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chili rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix rice and sour cream; add salt to taste.
Seed and chop chilies.
Grate cheeses.

title: jersey shore cioppino
directions: *Halibut or snapper or 2 pounds shellfish (any combination of clams, hard shell crabs' legs, shelled shrimp, oysters, etc.).

title: festive fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan combine first 4 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a full boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla until completely melted.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: brigettine monk's fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil; cook exactly 6 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove; add remaining ingredients.
Beat until firm. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and cool to room temperature.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix flour, salt, oregano, pepper, eggs and milk with mixer to make batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add pizza sauce to hamburger; pour over crust.
Add toppings of your choice:
onion, green peppers, mushrooms, pepperoni, black olives, etc.
Top with shredded cheese of your choice.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a 9 x 13-inch pan or pizza pan.
Sprinkle browned sausage on rolls.
Place cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cook spinach as per package directions.
Squeeze to remove as much moisture as possible.
Add onion and toss over moderate heat until all liquid has evaporated.
Remove from heat.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine crabmeat and lemon juice in a medium bowl and refrigerate while preparing sauce. Melt butter in medium saucepan. Add flour, stir and cook for about 1 minute. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, and cook until sauce thickens. Add seasonings and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth. Drain crabmeat and add to sauce; heat until bubbly. Layer cooked wild rice in bottom of a lightly greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Pour crabmeat and sauce over rice. Top with mushroom slices and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fat-free cream filled strawberries
directions: Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar until desired sweetness. Add a few drops of lemon extract.
Chill.
Remove core from strawberries.
Place cream in plastic bag.
Cut off corner and squeeze to pipe cream in strawberries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with enough water to cook them. When well done add milk, salt, pepper and butter (to taste). Bring to scalding point, then simmer for a while for the milk to gain flavor from the potatoes and onions.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Rub outside of squirrel with salt and pepper.
Marinate for several hours in mixture of egg and milk.
Remove from dish, dip in flour and deep fat fry for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: "chances are" hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add 3 teaspoons of mix to a cup. Fill cup with hot water.
Stir.
Put marshmallows on top.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions until thick.
Turn off heat.
Add margarine, cheeses, egg, salt and hot sauce.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Boil for 2 minutes in large pan, stirring constantly, the granulated sugar, margarine, cocoa powder and milk.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.
One or two spoonfuls make a cookie.
Let cool before you remove cookies from waxed paper.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until set.

title: tropical fruit dish
directions: In a small bowl, combine yogurt and orange juice concentrate. Place fruit in individual dessert bowls.
Drizzle each serving with yogurt sauce.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orange pickling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, oleo and eggs and beat.
Stir in mandarin oranges and juice.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Beat egg whites almost stiff.
Add baking powder; beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar, Ritz crackers, walnuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool slowly.

title: heart smart berry frost
directions: In covered blender at low speed, blend all ingredients until smooth and frothy.
Pour into glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Heat oil in a large kettle.
Cut steak in bite sized pieces.
Roll in seasoned flour and brown in oil.
When browned, add 2 cans of soup, plus 2 soup cans of water.
Cover and simmer until meat is fork-tender.
Add frozen noodles.
Cook, uncovered, until noodles are tender. Recipe may be doubled.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Fry bacon crisp and then break into pieces.
Saute green onion in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Remove from heat.
Scoop out inside of potato after they have been cut in half.
Add potato to the sauteed onion.
Add cheese and sour cream, salt and pepper and mash well.
Add bacon pieces.
Stuff potato shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together the cans of corn, the beaten eggs and the sugar. Make a paste of the milk and flour, then add to the corn mixture. Add the melted butter. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart Pyrex baking dish and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Shred chicken and mix with all ingredients except rice.
Cook about one hour over medium heat.
Pour sauce over prepared rice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine; put remaining ingredients in mixing bowl and pour melted margarine over all.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes, until done.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together in large bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil butter, shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add soda, milk and vanilla.
Combine egg mixture with flour mixture, mixing well.
Bake in greased 15 x 16 x 1-inch cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add flour and blend well. Add cream (half and half).
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Add seasonings and crab meat.
Stir well.
Before serving, spoon mixture into greased shells.
Top with crumbs and bits of butter.
Brown in the oven at 325°.
Can be made up ahead and put in the freezer.
Then bake as wanted.

title: six flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks which have been well beaten.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to cream mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Spoon into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Soak dates in hot water at 120° for 10 minutes.
Drain and refrigerate until cold.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt, water, baking soda, flour and pecans.
Mix only until combined.
Fold in dates.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: best french dressing
directions: Soak garlic for at least 30 minutes in vinegar.
Discard the garlic and mix in mustard, sugar, salt and paprika.
Add salad oil and mix well.
Use flavored vinegars to vary the taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into large baking dish.
Mix in next 4 ingredients. Place strips of bacon over beans and bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Bake uncovered.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Fold in chopped eggs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Can also be served in pastry shells or on toast.
Serves 15 to 18.
Half recipe makes plenty for a meal.
Reduce baking time to 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Mix together all liquid ingredients in the well. Mix the liquid and dry ingredients well.
Drop batter on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° to 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
36 cookies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake chicken and shred.
Brown 2 cups chicken in small amount of oil with onion and garlic.
Add enchilada sauce.
Roll chicken mixture in tortilla and place in pan.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together first five ingredients until blended well.
Blend in pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake 50 minutes.

title: grated potato cakes
directions: Mix together potatoes, onion, egg, flour and salt.
Heat oil in pan.
Drop potato mixture into pan, using a large spoon.
Brown cakes on one side.
Flatten with spoon.
Turn and brown on other side.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: After mixing ingredients, pour pudding into a greased 9 x 15-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Let cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares to serve.
These look like fudge brownies and are very moist.
Can be served with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: topsy-turvy pie
directions: Chop meat and saute until half done, then add onion.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate. Make Richer Biscuit.
Roll on floured surface and fit to top, cutting slits.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, then insert over a serving dish.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant and onion.
Boil or steam the eggplant in salted water until tender.
Add onion.

title: punch
directions: Combine
nectar and orange juice.
Add remaining ingredients just before serving.
After soda is added, float orange sherbet balls on top.
(Foams up like a sundae.)

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with grated cheese, dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Add corn chips and avocado. Brown ground beef and drain.
Add kidney beans and salt, simmer 10 minutes and mix into cold salad.
Decorate with extra chips, avocado and tomato if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: popovers(mom)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop a teaspoonful of dough in hot fryer (350° until brown).
Serve warm.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix together well.
Add enough flour for a stiff dough; roll on floured board until thin.
Let dry on cloth.
Cut into narrow strips and drop in boiling beef broth.
Cook 8 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add roux to chicken broth, milk and soup and cook until smooth.
Add the stuffing mix.
Add to this enough melted butter to moisten.
To make casserole:
Use 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Layer chicken using about 1/2 of the chicken.
Then layer 1/2 the sauce, 1/2 the dressing mix.
Repeat the layers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
This keeps well, it freezes well and it doubles well.
Serves 7 to 10.

title: scrambled veggie eggs(or omelet)
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in veggie pulp and stir.
Pour into skillet and scramble or make into omelet.
Season as desired.

title: baked peas
directions: Mix vinegar, horseradish, catsup, salt and Tabasco sauce together.
Pour over peas.
Add chopped eggs and dots of butter. Stir and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cornflakes over top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fig bread
directions: Cut raisins and figs into small pieces.
Cream shortening with honey until fluffy.
Add beaten egg; sift dry ingredients with
milk;
add
nuts
and fruits.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until clear and thickened.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Cool until slightly congealed.
Then add Milnot that has been whipped, Cool Whip or Dream Whip (prepared).
Place in large bowl and refrigerate.

title: chinese beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Mix all other ingredients with beef except noodles.
Put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Take out and top with noodles.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: honey crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine cereal, oats, nuts, cinnamon and salt.
In small saucepan, combine butter, honey and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter is melted and ingredients are well blended.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix until thoroughly coated.
Spread evenly into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is golden brown, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture onto wax paper covered cooling rack.
Stir in raisins.
Cool.
Store in container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk, and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce, and pecans.
Blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Freeze.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Crush crackers to make crumbs.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish for about 1 hour.

title: layered sombrero dip
directions: Blend beans and green chilies together.
Spread on platter. Top with sour cream, then guacamole, then salsa, then cheese, then lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peach crisp
directions: Spray baking dish with oil.
Arrange peaches in dish.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over peaches.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, oats, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix together and pour over peach mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°. Serves 8.

title: chocolate bananas
directions: You will need 6 popsicle sticks.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all together; eggs last.
Pour into buttered casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: sloppy joes(the kids' favorite)
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until tender.
Serve by spooning onto hamburger buns and with plenty of napkins!!!

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Pour mixture over apples and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Chop 2 to 3 onions and place in butter while it melts and simmer to soften onions.
Stir into cubes and salt to taste.
Add marjoram flakes and thyme sticks.
Season to taste.

title: side rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add rice and stir until golden brown. Remove from heat and add mushrooms, salt and pepper and dressing mix to the rice; stir well. Add enough hot water to reserved liquid to make 2 cups of liquid and pour over rice mix; bring to a boil. Pour into a buttered dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Put oil, meat, spices and sugar in skillet. Brown meat. Cover, stirring, until tender. Add soy sauce, green peppers, bean sprouts and onion. Cook, covered, about 5 minutes longer. Make paste of cornstarch and water.
Add to mixture.
Cook until thick. Serve over cooked rice.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices with sugar and put into cartons or containers to freeze.
Add 4 large bottles of ginger ale before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place a layer of lettuce on the bottom of a pan.
Cook and cool the peas.
Add peas on top of lettuce.
Layer the next 3 ingredients.
Mix the sour cream, mayo and Hidden Valley together. Pour over mixture.
Cut tomatoes in half and place on top of layers.
Add anything else you please.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Mix eggs, honey and milk and set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, evenly layer half of the bread cubes, then the cream cheese cubes and top with the rest of the bread.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with syrup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Fry peppers in oil.
Roll out bread dough and stretch into long loaf.
Place pepperoni, Provolone and peppers in center of dough (from top to bottom).
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Fold dough from sides to close loaf.
Brush oil on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: supreme old southern peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg; set aside until syrup forms.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and almond extract.
Cut pastry into 8-inch squares.
Spoon 1/2 peaches into pan; top with 1 square.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 minutes, or until crust is lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Spoon rest of peaches on crust.
Lattice with the rest of the crust.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, or until brown.
(This is a good way to make cobbler with any fresh fruit.)

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: my mom's caramel popcorn
directions: Mix the corn syrup, margarine and brown sugar together and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 full minute.
Remove mixture from heat.
Stir the salt, baking soda and vanilla into the mixture.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread popcorn into a greased roasting pan.
Pour caramel mixture over top of popcorn. Toss popcorn until completely coated with caramel mixture. Bake for 45 minutes in preheated 250° oven.
Halfway through cooking time, toss popcorn mixture.
Remove from oven when done.
Let cool in pan or spread in clumps on lightly greased waxed paper.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Great for snack time, camping, car trips, etc.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add milk last. Pour into a 6 x 12-inch greased dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients with 1/2 of the lemonade. Save the other 1/2.
Drop teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Brush immediately with remaining lemonade and sprinkle sugar on top.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water.
Let congeal slightly.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let congeal completely.

title: crustless bacon quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then drain on paper towels.
Combine eggs, milk, dash of pepper, baking mix and melted margarine in blender.
Cover and blend 15 seconds.
Pour mixture in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese well into mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix lightly with apples.
Pour into pie shell. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust; adjust and cut slits.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: weight watchers baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Fry onion in margarine, but do not brown.
In a quart dish, spread 3/4 cup macaroni.
Top with 1 1/2 ounces cheese and 1/2 the onion.
Repeat layers.
In a bowl, mix milk, egg, salt and pepper. Pour over macaroni and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving equals 2 protein, 1 1/2 bread, 1/2 vegetable, 1 fat and 3/4 milk.

title: betty's chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix everything together.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reba's hot-n-chunky chili
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in vegetable oil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add garlic, stirring 1 minute.
Remove to plate.
Add beef stir-fry in batches and cook until well browned, 5 to 6 minutes.
Return onion and garlic with beef to saucepan.
Add tomatoes and next 4 ingredients and water.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add green pepper.
Continue to simmer, stirring occasionally, another 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Chop into fine pieces the onion, avocados, chili pepper and tomato.
Then put in blender.
Add sour cream and hot sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend until smooth.

title: orange-lemon jello
directions: In 2 separate bowls dissolve orange jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve lemon jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Pour the lemon jello into blender and blend with 1/2 of cream cheese.
Pour into a bowl and refrigerate until lightly jelled.
Combine the remaining 1/2 of cream cheese with the orange jello in the blender; pour into container to refrigerate until slightly jelled.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Soak raisins in warm water.
Place sweet potatoes in large bowl and add sugar, milk, spices, eggs, salt and butter.
Mix well. Drain raisins and add to mixture.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until set.
During last part of cooking, marshmallows may be added on top to brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Mix with crumbled cornbread in casserole dish.
Drain vegetables and add to mixture.
Add soups.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until cornbread is brown and mixture is bubbling.

title: miniature cherry cheesecakes
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
In 2 dozen muffin tins, place paper liners.
In the bottom of each liner, place a vanilla wafer. Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese.
Mix in juice and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy. Spoon into liner.
Bake in a 375° oven just until set, about 15 minutes.
Remove cheese cake from muffin tins.
Do not remove liners.
Top each cheesecake with about 1 tablespoon pie filling. Refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve.

title: shrimp and clam bites
directions: Combine eggs and bread crumbs.
Stir in cheese, clams, shrimp, onions and pimiento.
Spread mixture in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Serve warm.
Makes 24.

title: pepparkakor(swedish ginger cookies)
directions: Beat together sugar and shortening.
Add molasses and blend well.
Add egg and continue mixing until egg is thoroughly blended. Mix 5 dry ingredients in a bowl and then sift into molasses mixture.
Chill at least one hour or overnight.

title: cappucchino-pistachio shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Dissolve coffee in water in medium bowl. Mix in margarine and powdered sugar.
Stir in flour and 1/2 cup nuts, using hands if necessary, until stiff dough forms.

title: colleen's stuffed bread
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until soft.
Put into large bowl when done.
Add olives and mushrooms to onion.
Brown and crumble sausage and ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add to onion mixture.
Add cheese.
Mix and let cool for about 15 minutes.
Then use fingers to mix and crumble mixture to even consistency.
Roll bread dough into 2 large rectangles (about 1/4-inch thick, 16 x 12-inch).
Spread mixture evenly on bread dough, leaving a 1/2-inch edge all around.
Roll bread into a log, pinching edges together as you go.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Place each loaf on a jelly roll sheet (or any baking dish with small sides).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave toasted pecans
directions: Spread pecans on microwave-safe plate.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir and add 1/4 stick margarine and salt to taste.
Toast 2 minutes, then spread on paper towel to cool.

title: peanut butter 'n chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat oleo, sugar and peanut butter in large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: quick chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook the spaghetti in salted water until tender. Drain. Combine with remaining ingredients, reserving half of cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a hot oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Lightly grease a baking tray. Sift flour, salt, mustard and baking powder in bowl. Rub in butter. Add all the milk; mix to a soft dough. Knead lightly until smooth. Roll out to just over 1/2-inch thick. Cut out with round cutter. Transfer to tray; bake 10 minutes until well-risen. Cool and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add vanilla and salt.
Sift together flour, baking powder and cocoa; add this alternately with milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.	Top with chips and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat together all ingredients, adding nuts last.
Put into heavily buttered pan covered with graham cracker crumbs.
Set cake pan in larger pan and add hot water to large pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan and add cabbage.
Fry slowly for 15 minutes.
Stir every few minutes.
Mix other ingredients and add to the cabbage.
Heat to the boiling point and serve.

title: super mexican dip
directions: Heat oil in a heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add beef and onions and cook until beef is brown, breaking up beef with a fork as it cooks, about 5 minutes.
drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon half of beans into 9x13-inch glass baking dish. Top with half of the beef, then half of the chilies, then half of the salsa, and then half of the cheese.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Bake dip until heated through and cheese melts, about 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream, green onions and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepared cake mix according to directions.
Pour into jelly roll pan, 10 x 15 in (greased) Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Blend pudding mix with milk.
Beat cream cheese into pudding; mix until smooth.
Stirring by hand, fold in whipping cream into pudding and cheese mixture.
Spread mixture over top and sides of cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries and coconut. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix water, coffee and sugar in a large pot.
Bring to full boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and vodka. Let cool.
Then bottle.
Let sit for 24 hours before using.
Makes 1 1/4 gallons.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Beat these ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake in three layers for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar, then let cool.
Let tea bags seep in boiling water and cool.
Mix everything in a large container and freeze.
Stir a couple of times while freezing.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Combine all except biscuits and cheese and place in 2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuits; cut into 20 half circles.
Place cut-side down around casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes
until tender.
Drain and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch
dish.
Saute onions in small amount of oleo or oil.
Mix onions
with
cream
cheese.
Add
sour
cream, then soup.	Pour over
potatoes,
then spread cheese on top of this mixture.
Top with
stuffing,
which you have mixed with oleo. Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Very good!

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate "wet" cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large mixer bowl. Bring to a boil and pour over sugar and flour the margarine, cocoa, Crisco and water. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Batter will be very thin and may spatter. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 400° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ground round casserole
directions: Make patties and place in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Slice potatoes and layer over top of meat.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Layer frozen veggies over potatoes.
Chop onion and layer over top of veggies.
Add mushrooms.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.

title: cheese spread
directions: Use food processor to chop onion.
Then add Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Add Tabasco and salt, if desired.
Process until smooth and creamy.
Layer cheese and pecans in serving dish and spread on crackers (Triscuits taste great!).

title: ice cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour.
Let cool.
Cream Crisco, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Put all ingredients together and beat until creamy.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook unpared potatoes covered in boiling salted water (1/2 teaspoon to 1 cup water) 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Cool slightly.
Peel and cut up into cubes.
Toss with onions, salt, pepper and Italian dressing.
Cover.
Chill thoroughly at least 8 hours.

title: broccoli crab bisque(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook leeks, mushrooms, broccoli and garlic in butter until crisp-tender.
Blend in flour, thyme (1/8 teaspoon salt, optional), pepper and bay leaf.
Add chicken broth and cream all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add crabmeat; heat through.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
In large pot, mix refried beans, chili beans, taco mixture, Tabasco sauce, tomato paste, sauce and 1 tomato paste can of water.
Cook all together for 20 minutes and then let it simmer until ready to eat.
In plate, layer tortilla chips, taco mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese and top with sour cream.

title: cherrywine chocolate cake
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Over medium heat, combine first 3 ingredients and cook until soft ball forms.
Take off stove and add last 3 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour into long, greased cake pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Can be stored several days in refrigerator.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Combine asparagus, celery soup, eggs and cheese.
Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and crumbs are golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peach dessert
directions: Pour jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Make sure jello is dissolved good.
Pour in 2 cups of cold water.
Add peach pie filling.
Put in bowl and chill.

title: chicken strips with rosemary and marsala wine
directions: Lightly flour strips.
Heat pan and add olive oil, 2 tablespoons butter and garlic (watch garlic does not burn).
Fry chicken strips lightly in batches.
Tent with foil on a serving platter.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon of oil and add rosemary to garlic in pan.
Fry over medium heat about 2 minutes.
Add Marsala wine and deglaze pan.
Boil until reduced by 1/2.
Take off heat and add remaining butter.
Strain contents of pan over chicken. Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: chicken and sausage pileau
directions: Boil chicken about 45 minutes or until done.
Cool; remove from bone.
Set aside in bowl.
Cut sausage into pieces.
In large pot, combine oil and sausage.
Brown, stirring occasionally.
Add onion; simmer about 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook on medium heat about 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, chicken and 4 cups water.
Bring to boil; add rice.
Cook on medium 15 minutes, then simmer for 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until rice is done.

title: sleep 'n bake cookies
directions: Heat
oven
to
Line
2 cookie sheets with foil. Beat egg
whites
until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in butterscotch chips and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil. Do not
let touch or overcrowd.
Turn oven off and put cookies in. Go
to
bed.
The
next morning store cookies in airtight container.

title: three layer salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cherries and pour into a lightly oiled mold or dish.
Chill until set. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese; add milk and mix well.
Add lemon Jell-O to cream cheese mixture, mixing well.
Spoon over cherry Jell-O layer. Chill until set.
Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in marshmallows and let partly dissolve.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in pineapple.
Spoon mixture over lemon Jell-O layer.
Add pecans to top and chill until firm.

title: wonderful bars
directions: Mix all ingredients with chips folded in last.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch rectangular pan or dish (greased).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients by hand and shape into small balls; refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt in double boiler chocolate bar and paraffin wax.
Dip balls into chocolate and wax mixture. Place on wax paper; refrigerate in airtight container.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add meat and brown well, then add onion, garlic, green peppers, celery, salt, pepper and consomme.
Cover and cook gently for about 1 hour. Blend cornstarch with water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture and cook uncovered 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chris' favorite no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan the melted margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute and then take off heat.
Add peanut butter, cocoa, vanilla and quick oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or foil.

title: hot jerky
directions: Marinate meat in mixture overnight or at least 12 hours.
Stir or shake occasionally.
Dehydrate at 145° for about 4 hours or until done.
If using a smoker, omit the liquid smoke.
Use generous spoonfuls of spices.

title: reuben dip a-la-val
directions: Shred cheese and corned beef.
Chop onion.
Throw together in crock-pot until cheese is melted and mixed thoroughly with the rest.
Serve on cocktail rye.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Heat oil and butter in Dutch oven.
Add onion and paprika; cook until brown.
Stir in salt and chicken stock; bring mixture to a boil.
Add chicken and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir together flour and sour cream and stir into chicken mixture.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve with dumplings (or rice).

title: banana split bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg. In a small bowl, combine bananas and milk. Combine the flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana mixture. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown in a heavy skillet with butter.
Arrange in pan approximately 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches.
Blend soup with drippings in skillet.
Stir wine (or other liquid) in slowly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oreo blow out
directions: Mix milk and pudding together.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Crumble just enough Oreos to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture.
Crumble rest of Oreos and top with whipped cream.
I have even saved enough of the Oreos and sprinkled them on top of whipped cream.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Have all ingredients ready, including buttered plate; this is very quick!

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into shells.
Refrigerate until firm (can be frozen).
When ready to serve, sprinkle with coconut, nuts or cherries, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use glass or Corning Ware pie plate (8 to 9-inch).
Combine sugar, butter and water; microwave for 1 minute.
Add nuts and stir.
Cut each biscuit into 4 equal pieces, add to sugar mixture and roll to coat each piece.
Use rubber spatula to scrape mixture and biscuits from center to place empty custard cup into, open end up.
Cook at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, or can be microwaved instead of using oven for 1 minute, turned halfway and microwaved for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until biscuits are not sticky.
Remove and take custard cup out with potholder.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and next 6 ingredients.
Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in hot oil; add meat and seasonings.
Brown lightly.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add soups and 1 can of water; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse with hot water. Arrange on hot platter; pour sauce over and sprinkle with cheese.

title: flounder florentine
directions: In saucepan, cook onion with rosemary in oil until tender. Add spinach, rice, almonds and lemon juice. Heat slowly; stir occasionally.
Arrange fish fillets in an 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; place spinach and rice mixture evenly on top.
