Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then blend soup, water and lemon pepper; pour over spinach mixture and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, until bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Add coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in layers.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over top.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch layered dessert
directions: Bottom Crust:
Mix flour, 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and butter.
Pat on bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in 3 (9-inch) layer pans.

title: ragu sauce lasagna
directions: Cook carrot, onion, celery and garlic in small amount of olive oil until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, oregano, parsley and bouillon.
Stir all together and cook on low heat for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in hot oil and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in same pot.
Add more oil, if needed.
Return meat to pot.
Add all remaining ingredients, except chili peppers and cornmeal. Cover and simmer over low heat until meat is tender and liquid is reduced (2 to 3 hours).
Add cornmeal to thicken, if needed.
Add chili peppers.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: sherry slap pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snow nut balls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together and work in butter, vanilla and nuts with hands.
Shape into bite size balls.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
While still a little warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
(You can put at least 35 balls on one cookie sheet.
It doesn't spread anywhere.)

title: cheddar cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and 1 cup cheese into mixing bowl.
Combine milk, oleo and eggs; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon; top with green pepper.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mildred's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together corn syrup, beaten eggs, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30-40 minutes longer or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie. Don't overbake.

title: apple dumplings with syrup
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in Crisco and add milk.
Mix well until moist.
Roll out and cut in squares.
Place some apple slices in each square and wrap dough around apples; seal.
Place in greased pan and pour syrup over each dumpling.

title: apple smiles
directions: Cut apples into 8 slices each.
Remove seeds and cores. Spread peanut butter on one side of each slice.
Place marshmallows between 2 apple slices like a sandwich.

title: homemade sour cream pound cake(my recipe)
directions: Blend all ingredients into a large mixing bowl on low speed, increasing to medium speed for 4 minutes.
Grease and flour
a tube pan or just spray with Pam.
Place in cold oven.
Set oven at 375° and bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Keep an eye on it.
Partially cool in pan, then remove from pan.
Cool and glaze afterwards, if wanted.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook
your
favorite
pasta according to package directions. Don't
salt.
Don't
overcook.
While
pasta
cooks, slice/cut your
favorite
salad
vegetables
into
bite-size pieces: cucumbers,
tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green peppers,
onions, etc.
Put vegetables into large bowl; sprinkle with
dried
Italian
salad
dressing mix (amount is determined by your taste and amount of vegetables).
Drain and rinse cooked pasta.
Allow
to
cool
somewhat.
Add pasta to vegetables; sprinkle with more dried dressing mix.
Mix well. When ready
to serve, add bottled Italian salad dressing.
For a change, add cubed pepperoni, cheese, black olives, etc.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add yolks and mix well.
Add lemon extract and mix.

title: apple breakfast sandwiches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Separate biscuits and press each into a 3-inch circle.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet; sprinkle with cheese and top each with an apple ring.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden.
Serve immediately.
May serve with bacon or sausage, if desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon pie filling evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread pineapple on top of that.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix. Pour margarine over all.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: golden pastry
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
With a pastry blender or two knives, cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse oatmeal.
Add water one tablespoon at a time and mix lightly with a fork until all flour is moistened.
With the hands, gather dough into a ball and divide in half.
On a lightly floured board, roll out each half in a circle 1/8-inch thick and about 1 1/2-inches larger in diameter than a pie plate.
Yield:
2 pie shells.

title: peppy skillet eggs
directions: In skillet, cook green pepper in butter until tender.
In a bowl, stir soup until smooth. Blend in eggs, corn and pepper sauce.
Pour into skillet. Gently stir until cooked.
Garnish with cheese.

title: ball field chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
If desired, chopped onion and green pepper may be added when browning meat.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook rice separately.
Chop shrimp and set aside.
Heat oil and add onions,
celery,
bell
pepper and garlic in cast-iron skillet.
Cook,
uncovered, over medium heat until onions are soft.
Add tomato paste and cook, stirring constantly, for about 15 minutes.
Add
cup
water.
Season with salt and peppers. Add sugar
and cook, uncovered, over medium heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp;
continue cooking and stirring
another
20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water and add; cook another 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice, green onion tops and parsley, mixing well.

title: ozgood pie(spiced pecan and raisins)
directions: Beat eggs, add	sugar and butter, spices, then vinegar, pecans and raisins.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and butter. Place in greased baking dish.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Cut 3 lbs of fish to bite sized chunks.
(Carp)

title: marinade for grilled london broil
directions: In large Ziploc bag combine all your ingredients.
Place steak in bag and marinate overnight. Grill to desired doneness.
Best if rare or medium rare.
Cut beef across grain at slanted angle into thin slices.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven "fried" fish
directions: Combine flour and seasonings in plastic bag.
Shake well.
Dip fish fillets in the mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and pour into a casserole dish (including liquid from mixed vegetables).
Sprinkle cheese on top of this mixture.
Top with croutons and melted margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: lo-cal apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples and let them sit for 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a small bowl.
In one pie shell, place apples in shell and pour sugar mixture over apples evenly.
Place other pie shell on top and sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on top and cut holes to vent in top crust.
Press edges of pie shells together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix soup, wine and cheese.
Put chicken in a 9 X 13 pan and cover with the soup mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine and drizzle over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Slice bananas over mixture.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake.
Put cherries and crushed nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lazy cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat up vegetable oil in skillet.
Run the tortillas through the oil one at a time.
Run them through quickly.
In remainder of oil, pour the enchilada sauce.
Add salt.
Heat until it boils. In separate bowl, mix onions and cheese.
Dip oiled tortillas into the sauce, then put cheese in middle of tortilla and roll it up. Do this to every tortilla.
Heat enchiladas in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve enchiladas on top of lettuce.
Garnish with sour cream, olives and Parmesan cheese.

title: favorite cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and salt and pepper in a bowl. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan. Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in chafing dish.
Yields 70 meatballs.

title: microwave oven fried chicken
directions: Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken. Arrange pieces, skin side up, in microwave dish with thickest parts to outside edges.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 10 minutes.
Rotate dish half turn and microwave until done, 8 to 12 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix hamburger which has been cooked and drained with cubed Velveeta and chili.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Put in crock-pot.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: peanut butter n chocolate chip cookies
directions: 350° oven.
Beat margarine, sugars, and peanut butter in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoons on to ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10-12 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: catch of the day plank fish
directions: You will need one 12 x 18-inch board.

title: majik cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix graham cracker crumbs in butter to make the crust.
Pour milk over crust in bottom as evenly as possible.
Spread chips over milk, then coconut over that and then the nuts over the whole thing.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: frosted walnuts
directions: Mix the buttermilk and sugar. Cook slowly until soft ball stage, approximately 15 minutes. Take off heat. Add the vanilla, then the nuts.
Stir until covered. Spread on wax paper in pan. Break apart with fork. Store in tin.
Delicious!

title: cherry pudding
directions: Whip the cream.
Add Dream Whip and beat until stiff.
Pour in cherries and cream; stir good.
Crumble vanilla wafers and stir into mixture.
Roll out 1/2 cup of vanilla wafers to a very fine crumb.
Sprinkle on top of pudding.
Put in freezer for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mabel saltsman's cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients to blend.
Beat until light and fluffy (adding very small amounts of milk, if necessary for desired consistency).
Spread on cooled cake.
Usually enough "left over" to ice graham crackers.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix jello with water; set aside.
Mix cake mix, oil and eggs; beat.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add jello; beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add soda to water; add to creamed mixture and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and dates.
Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full each and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
You can use 4 loaf pans.
Can be frozen.

title: spoon yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Beat in yeast mixture and flour.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen. Dough keeps in refrigerator for four weeks.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 1/4-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand.
Brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture and cook, stirring until clear and thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: *My preference is Golden Delicious.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in airtight container. Add 2 to 3 teaspoons of dry mixture to a hot cup of water. Guaranteed to take the chill off any winter day!

title: potatoes and onion
directions: Put diced potatoes in a pan.
Dab butter on top.
Sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° at least one hour. The last 10 minutes, top with cheese and continue baking, uncovered.

title: spice tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Store in an airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of boiling water to make 1 cup of Spice Tea.

title: stew with beef and pork sandwiches
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour or until meat is tender.

title: hungry jake biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Stir in sauce, onion and sugar.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors.
Place 1 biscuit into each muffin pan. Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into each biscuit.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: lime jello surprise
directions: Chill jello to thickening. Cut up cheese into small pieces. Blend, leaving a few chunks. Add walnuts. Chill.

title: great pumpkin cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter, gradually add sugars, beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin; mix well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.
For each cookie drop 1/4 cup dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet, spread into pumpkin shape, using a thin metal spatula.
Add a bit more dough to form stem.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until cookies are firm and lightly brown.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool on racks.
Decorate, using icing or peanut butter to affix assorted candies, raisins or nuts.
Yields 19 to 20 cookies.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour alternately with milk. Add flavoring.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: supreme sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool until lukewarm.
Soak yeast in lukewarm water only for 5 minutes, then add to milk mixture.
Add eggs.
Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour 1 cup at a time to make a stiff dough.
Put in greased muffin tins and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Using the yogurt carton as a measure, put all the ingredients into a bowl and beat well.
Pour the mixture into a greased and lined 9-inch diameter round cake tin.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours in electric at 160°C.
Allow to cool in tin.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar (a little at a time) and beat until sugar is gone.
Add one egg and small portion of cake flour and beat well.
Do this until all flour is used.
Add dash of salt, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Beat well (total mixture).
Bake at 300° until cake is done (if an inserted toothpick comes out dry, cake is done).

title: marinated steak salad
directions: Slash fat edges of steak.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn and broil until done (medium 6 to 9 minutes). Cool.
Cut into thin slices.
Place steak in plastic bag in bowl.

title: cheese puffs (easy)
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together; add flour and milk. Blend well and form a large ball with your hands.
Roll little balls with your hands (size of large marble).
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes only.
Serve hot.

title: best ever potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on for approximately 25 minutes. Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Butter casserole.
Scrape off skin from potatoes and grate on medium food grater.
Layer in casserole the potatoes, onion salt, salt, pepper, grated cheese and dot with butter.
Repeat for second layer.
Cover with cream and sprinkle top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be prepared the day before and add cream just before baking.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Real good with baked ham.

title: buttery bread pudding
directions: In a buttered casserole (9 x 9-inch), put bread. Sprinkle butter over bread.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk. Pour mixture over bread. Sprinkle a little more cinnamon over top.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Put the following layers in a large rectangle baking dish or plastic container at least 10 x 6-inches in size:

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain and rinse salmon in cold water twice.
Place in a large mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients. Thoroughly mix. Form into small balls. Drop into preheated oil in a deep fryer (peanut oil gives the best flavor).
Drain on paper towels.
You can serve hot or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: micro rice pudding
directions: Microwave 8 minutes on High, then 15 minutes on 30% to 50% in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Maintain simmer.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix popcorn, cereal and peanuts in large bowl.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly to boiling.
Cook without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Drizzle over popcorn mixture; toss lightly until evenly coated.
Spoon into large shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring several times, 1 hour.
Cool and store in a lightly covered container.

title: elegant zucchini(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Wash zucchini and boil in lightly salted water about 10 minutes or just until barely tender.
Drain.
Cut off ends and slice in half lengthwise.
Arrange in buttered casserole.
Mix melted butter with cheeses, sour cream, salt, paprika and chives and pour over zucchini.
Spread bread crumbs evenly on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle generously with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip , milk and caramel sauce with blender or mixer. Bake 2 pie shells and cool.
Put a layer of mixture.
Top with toasted pecans and coconut.
Top this with caramel sauce.
Layer with same stuff again and freeze.
Thaw a little before serving.

title: molasses cutouts
directions: Mix together thoroughly margarine, sugar, egg and molasses. Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon. Chill dough at least 2 hours.
Roll out thick (1/4-inch).
Cut into desired shapes.
Cool and frost as desired.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: honey glazed veal chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except veal chops, in a glass dish, stirring to blend and coat the onion rings.
Add the veal and marinate 24 hours in the refrigerator.
The marinade should cover the meat.
Remove from the refrigerator about 30 minutes before grilling.
Place onion rings on a square of heavy-duty foil and form a tight pouch.
Place pouch on grill and preheat the grates about 15 minutes, covered.
Grill the chops over medium heat approximately 10 minutes on the first side and 5 minutes on the second until glazed and browned.
Remove to a warm platter.
Open foil pouch and place onion rings on chops before serving.
Cut reserved lemon rind into rings for garnish.

title: lemonade icebox pie
directions: Mix lemonade, milk and salt together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in vanilla wafer pie crust.
Top with pecans.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: fruit gelatin punch
directions: Prepare gelatins according to directions, using half the amount of water called for.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen juices according to directions on the can. Add remaining sugar; mix well.
Add ginger ale, just before serving.
Makes approximately 50 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough (if needed).
Roll into balls about walnut size.
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Should be soft.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Flatten the biscuits.
Place 1/2 hot dog on biscuit and wrap around hot dog.
Place on baking pan.
Put in 350° preheated oven until brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve with catsup and mustard.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Line a pie tin with unbaked crust and put in rhubarb (cut fine). Mix well the remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb. Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: world's simplest rhubarb pie
directions: Mix milk, egg, rhubarb and cinnamon.
Turn mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Very good and fast!!

title: party punch
directions: Combine water and sugar in a small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: 7 day slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except vegetables. Mix well.
Add vegetables and toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate for up to 7 days.

title: peach glaze pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and slowly cook over low heat until clear (about 5 minutes).
Add yellow food coloring and cool slightly.
Wash and pare peaches.
Cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
Place in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over each layer of peaches.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Mix vanilla water crumbs, margarine and 1 tsp. Equal for Recipes in bottom of 9 inch springform pan.
Reserve 1 Tbsp. of crumb mixture.
Pat remaining mixture evenly on bottom and 1/2 inch up side of pan.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven until crust is lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Beat cream cheese and 5 1/2 tsp. Equal for Recipes in a large bowl until fluffy; beat in eggs, egg whites and cornstarch.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla until well blended.
Pour mixture into crust in pan.
Place cheesecake in roasting pan on oven rack; add 1 inch hot water to the roasting pan.
Bake in preheated 300 degree oven just until set in the center, 45 to 60 minutes. Remove cheesecake from roasting pan, sprinkle with reserved crumbs and return to oven.
Turn oven off and let cheesecake cool in oven with door ajar for 3 hours.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Remove side of pan; place cheesecake on serving plate.
Serve with fresh fruit and Strawberry Sauce, the recipe of which follows. Makes 16 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together well; add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
If zucchini is very large, peel and take out seeds.

title: chili
directions: Cut onions, garlic and pepper into small pieces and fry until lightly brown.
Brown ground beef, stirring constantly with a potato masher (to keep from balling up).
Pour into large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy barbecue wieners
directions: Slice wieners and place in a baking dish.
Pour sauce and water over wieners and sprinkle chopped onions in.
Stir.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Great at parties as an appetizer.

title: chicken casserole(good)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, and place in greased casserole.
Top with potato chips and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 10.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix the peaches with the 3/4 cup sugar and melted butter in pan in oven set at 350°. Stir together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Pour mixture over butter. Do not stir. Spoon peaches over batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; add Ragu and tomato paste.
Cook noodles. Mix Ricotta cheese and Cottage cheese with egg.
Salt and pepper cheese mixture to taste.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture and sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers with noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture and shredded Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarinade
directions: Mix together!
Ready to sell at the local Mandarinade stand!

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Stir in milk and egg.
Fry teaspoonful of batter in hot fat in frying pan until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with fish or meat.
Makes 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: economy fruit cake
directions: Boil water, raisins and fruit for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening and spices. Cool overnight.

title: indian chili
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add beef and stir constantly until separated well.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook until tomatoes are cooked to pieces and mixture is thick.
Add chili powder and beans.
Let simmer awhile.
Serve with cheese, pickles and crackers.

title: baker's clay
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly with hands. If dough is too stiff to handle, add more water, a little at a time.
Remove dough from bowl.
Knead for 4 to 5 minutes.
Shape into desired ornaments.
Bake on cookie sheets in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or more, depending on size and thickness of pieces; some may take 2 hours or longer.
Test for doneness with fork or toothpick in thickest part of piece.
If still soft, bake a little longer.
Lift pieces from cookie sheet with spatula. Cool on racks.
When thoroughly cooled, paint or decorate.
Spray finished pieces with a clear fixative when decorated, to prevent softening.

title: jello-pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted butter and crushed pretzels.
Press into a glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; refrigerate to cool.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt bark in double boiler and add peanut butter.
Stir often and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir with wooden spoon.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, carrots, celery and onion in water about 1 hour or simmer until tender.
Remove bones from chicken and break up in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together soup and sour cream and cover chicken with mixture.
Sprinkle top with stuffing and butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cashew oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla. Beat well.

title: hash
directions: Cut pork steaks in small squares.
Fry in skillet with onion until meat is tender.
Cut potatoes in cubes and cover meat with potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Pour mushroom soup and water over the meat and potatoes and simmer on low heat about 25 minutes.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Dice the corned beef and onions; set aside.
Slightly melt the cream cheese and add the can of soup.
(Add no water.) Mix well. Add the beef and onions.
Mix well.
Best when refrigerated for 1 to 2 hours.
Ritz crackers are good for this dip.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and lemon colored.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Cook in saucepan until smooth.
Stir constantly; cool. Place pineapple chunks, oranges, apples, grapes and bananas in large salad bowl.
Mix gently.
Add egg mixture and mix gently. Add sugar and vanilla to whipped cream.
Fold marshmallows and cream into fruit.
Chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: evelyn's chicken dijon
directions: Combine salad dressing and mustard.
Coat chicken with mixture and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy!

title: good n easy pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and oil.
Stir.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Dough should be fairly stiff, but not dry.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Oil pans well.
Press dough onto pans with hands.
Put toppings desired.
Bake at 425° until brown and bubbly (around 15 minutes).

title: apple butter spice cake
directions: Cut butter into pieces and put in a 9-inch square cake pan. Place in a preheated 350° oven until butter is melted, about 5 minutes.
Remove the pan from the oven and tilt it so that the butter coats the bottom and sides.
Set aside.
In large bowl crumble brown sugar over apple butter.
Add butter, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in the melted butter from the pan.
Whisk until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and salt to the apple butter mixture and whisk just until combined. Fold in raisins and apple.
Spread the batter in the prepared pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top feels firm when lightly pressed in the center.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and reserve broth.
Debone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix all the ingredients together in large bowl. Add chicken.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add glaze and cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack.

title: delicious potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Also boil eggs until they are hard-boiled.
Allow potatoes and eggs to cool.
In saucepan, combine the flour, sugar, 1 egg, water, vinegar, mustard and salt. Cook until thick.
Remove from burner and add margarine.
Allow to cool.
Peel and dice both potatoes and eggs.
Chop onion.
Mix together the potatoes, onion, relish and cooked dressing.
Allow to chill overnight.

title: scalloped oysters(my mother's recipe)
directions: Heat oysters in their own juice.
Lightly saute pepper and onion in butter; add flour.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the seasonings, then add the oysters.
Fold in the cracker meal. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut round steak in strips 1/8-inch thick and 2-inches long. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge steak strips in seasoned flour.
Brown in lard or drippings.
Pour off drippings.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water, then add along with onions, Burgundy, ketchup, parsley sprigs, bay leaf, thyme and garlic powder to meat.
Add carrots, if desired.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Remove parsley and bay leaf.
Thicken gravy with flour, if necessary.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: fresh rhubarb cake
directions: Spread rhubarb evenly in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O (dry).
Sprinkle sugar over Jell-O.
Add marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix as directed on the box.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set for 20 minutes before turning over.

title: cheese fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together
with an electric mixer on medium speed. Chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with sliced apples or any fruit of your choice.

title: easy round steak
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 package soup mix in bottom of pan.
Place steak on top of soup mix.
Add rest of soup mix and then add mushrooms and water.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package direction and bake in a 9x13 pan.

title: applesauce roll
directions: Beat well all together.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum wrap. Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon with chive mayonnaise
directions: In a bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; set aside 1/3 cup for serving. Place salmon steaks on a broiler rack. Broil 4-inches from the heat for 9 minutes. Brush with remaining mayonnaise mixture. Turn salmon over; broil 9 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with fork. Serve with the reserved mayonnaise mixture. Yield: 2 servings.

title: "candace's" delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake until brown; cool (at least 15 minutes).
Mix the Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust. Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk; spread over chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with nuts for garnish.

title: brown sugar walnut pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Add Jello to the boiling water and stir until Jello dissolves well and let cool.
Mix ice cream and cool whip together and add cold peaches.
Then pour in the cool jello and water mixture. Pour in the ready cooked deep pie shell and refrigerate until firm.

title: dilly appetizers
directions: Combine ketchup, cream cheese, lemon juice, dill, lemon peel and garlic powder.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Spoon small amount of dressing on each zucchini slice.
Top with shrimp. Garnish with fresh dill, if desired.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise scrub good and rinse. Cut into thin slices (but not all the way through).
Fan open and sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs or spices.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 or 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: apples and carrots casserole
directions: Place 1 can of apples with apple liquid in buttered casserole. Cover with carrots.
Dot with butter.
Combine sugars, flour and salt.
Sprinkle half the sugar mixture over the apples and carrots. Sprinkle with a little nutmeg and cinnamon.
Repeat layers.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tiny pecan pies
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Divide dough into 24 small balls and press into tiny muffin tins to make crust.
Pour filling into crust.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
